WEBVTT

00:12.689 --> 00:14.896
[ominous music playing]

00:41.297 --> 00:43.856
[wind whistling]

00:47.121 --> 00:48.592
[owl hooting]

00:48.720 --> 00:50.225
[podcaster 1] <i>What do you even</i>
<i>have to back it up?</i>

00:50.352 --> 00:52.113
[podcaster 2]
<i>There were eyewitnesses.</i>

00:52.240 --> 00:55.921
<i>A man fitting</i>
<i>Macher's description</i>
<i>was spotted at a sorority party</i>

00:56.048 --> 00:57.681
<i>at Windsor College in 1997.</i>

00:57.809 --> 00:59.569
<i>The same year</i>
<i>the murders took place.</i>

00:59.697 --> 01:01.297
[podcaster 1 scoffs]
<i>It's complete speculation,</i>

01:01.425 --> 01:02.737
<i>all right?</i>
<i>That's never been confirmed.</i>

01:02.864 --> 01:04.177
[podcaster 2]
<i>It has been con--</i>

01:08.113 --> 01:09.201
[sighs]

01:09.329 --> 01:10.865
Holy shit.

01:10.993 --> 01:12.560
[passenger] Ugh,
that was a long drive.

01:12.688 --> 01:14.512
[driver chuckles]

01:16.881 --> 01:18.897
Holy fucking shit!

01:19.025 --> 01:20.753
Can you get
a photo of me?

01:20.881 --> 01:22.192
Yeah.

01:24.753 --> 01:26.577
All right. Cute.

01:26.705 --> 01:27.537
[shutter clicking]

01:27.665 --> 01:28.465
[shouts]

01:28.593 --> 01:29.585
[passenger chuckles]

01:29.712 --> 01:32.081
I got it.
[chuckles]

01:32.880 --> 01:34.448
Wait, one more.
One more.

01:34.897 --> 01:35.889
[groans]

01:38.001 --> 01:40.368
Okay, I have to pee.
Let's go inside.

01:40.496 --> 01:44.208
The code is...
[sighs, groans]

01:45.104 --> 01:49.457
...7-8-2-2.

01:49.585 --> 01:51.088
[lock clicks]

01:51.441 --> 01:52.912
[chuckles]

01:54.289 --> 01:57.712
Are you ready for...
[lock clicking]

01:59.313 --> 02:02.801
...the Macher House Experience?

02:02.929 --> 02:03.921
Wow.

02:04.625 --> 02:06.609
Oh.
[switch clicks]

02:07.825 --> 02:09.937
Oh, my God.
Ugh.

02:10.064 --> 02:11.984
Incredible.
Whoa.

02:12.112 --> 02:13.008
[driver chuckles]

02:13.136 --> 02:15.441
A real-life murder house.

02:15.569 --> 02:17.137
It's perfect.
[sighs]

02:17.680 --> 02:19.089
Mm-hmm.
Right?

02:19.856 --> 02:21.744
I mean, it's like--
it's identical.

02:24.017 --> 02:25.041
Oh, this is cool.

02:25.169 --> 02:26.929
The fake blood.
Mm-hmm.

02:27.440 --> 02:28.496
Oh! [driver laughs]

02:28.625 --> 02:30.097
Check it out. Check it out.

02:30.224 --> 02:31.184
[groans]

02:31.312 --> 02:32.817
Ugh, I'm gonna pee my pants.

02:32.945 --> 02:34.224
[imitates gagging]
[shutter clicks]

02:34.353 --> 02:36.305
Babe, this is
where Sidney Prescott

02:36.433 --> 02:38.289
shot Billy Loomis in the face
right after she--

02:38.417 --> 02:40.720
Stabbed him with
the umbrella. I know.

02:40.848 --> 02:42.129
Where's the bathroom?

02:42.257 --> 02:43.696
Oh, no, that's the closet
Sidney was hiding in.

02:43.824 --> 02:45.873
Remember? Before she stabbed
him with the umbrella?

02:46.001 --> 02:47.025
Duh.

02:48.785 --> 02:50.065
[sighs]

02:52.336 --> 02:53.713
Oh, I found it!

02:53.841 --> 02:55.376
Oh. [chuckles]

02:55.825 --> 02:57.329
So cool.

03:01.489 --> 03:02.673
Ah.

03:02.800 --> 03:05.105
This is so cool!

03:06.193 --> 03:07.696
Incredible.

03:09.552 --> 03:10.929
Amber.

03:11.057 --> 03:12.849
And Richie. I mean...

03:14.929 --> 03:15.921
[shutter clicks]

03:17.009 --> 03:17.905
Ooh.

03:18.033 --> 03:19.505
[footsteps receding]

03:28.465 --> 03:29.712
Scott?

03:30.800 --> 03:32.817
[ominous music plays]

03:35.761 --> 03:37.009
Scott?

03:38.897 --> 03:40.400
Hello?

03:47.281 --> 03:48.848
Scott!

03:51.185 --> 03:53.009
Dude, where'd you go?

04:03.248 --> 04:04.432
[metal clinking]

04:05.296 --> 04:06.769
[screams]

04:08.080 --> 04:09.457
[breathing heavily]

04:10.545 --> 04:11.793
[both scream]

04:11.920 --> 04:14.065
Whoa. What's wrong?
Oh, my God!
Ghostface is in there!

04:14.193 --> 04:14.832
What?

04:14.960 --> 04:15.824
Ghostface is in there!

04:15.953 --> 04:16.816
Someone with a ghost mask on.

04:16.945 --> 04:18.065
What are you talking about?

04:18.193 --> 04:19.345
There's somebody in that room

04:19.473 --> 04:20.817
with a Ghostface mask on.

04:20.945 --> 04:21.873
Oh...

04:22.001 --> 04:23.472
[breathes shakily]
Do not go in there.

04:23.600 --> 04:25.585
Scott. Scott!

04:30.993 --> 04:33.136
[ominous music plays]

04:37.553 --> 04:38.864
[gasps]
Ooh!

04:38.993 --> 04:40.816
<i>You're going</i>
<i>to die tonight!</i>
[chuckles]

04:43.473 --> 04:44.656
It's fake.

04:48.400 --> 04:51.153
Oh, that is so cool.

04:51.280 --> 04:53.200
It's got a motion sensor.

04:53.328 --> 04:54.993
Look at this.

04:55.120 --> 04:57.168
<i>Do you like scary movies?</i>

04:57.297 --> 04:59.345
[Scott]
I mean, come on, look at that.

04:59.473 --> 05:02.289
[sensor whirring]
That's so cool.

05:02.864 --> 05:04.049
Pretty hi-tech.

05:04.593 --> 05:06.065
It looked so real.

05:06.193 --> 05:08.913
That is sweet!

05:09.520 --> 05:10.673
Wow.

05:10.801 --> 05:14.193
It's plugged in
right here.
What?

05:14.320 --> 05:16.689
Ah, so this is it.
This is so creepy.

05:16.817 --> 05:18.577
The room where
Stu held that party

05:18.705 --> 05:20.497
to lure Sidney Prescott
to her death.

05:20.625 --> 05:23.024
You know, they say Billy
was the mastermind,

05:23.153 --> 05:25.936
but I've always been
more of a Stu-head.

05:26.065 --> 05:27.025
Who was your favorite?
What?

05:27.153 --> 05:29.393
My favorite
homicidal teenager?

05:29.521 --> 05:30.545
Neither.

05:31.345 --> 05:32.721
Are you gonna be like this
the whole time?

05:32.849 --> 05:34.257
What do you want me to do?

05:34.705 --> 05:35.761
[mutters] Um...

05:35.889 --> 05:37.649
Okay. Babe,
did you know that this is

05:37.777 --> 05:39.537
where Sidney dropped a TV
on Stu's head?

05:39.665 --> 05:41.713
Squished all the crazy
out of his brain?

05:41.841 --> 05:44.176
Ah, but did she kill him?

05:44.305 --> 05:47.761
You heard the podcast.
There's a lot of theories
out there that Stu survived.

05:47.888 --> 05:49.137
[passenger] No.
There was a dead body.

05:49.265 --> 05:51.792
It was taken to the morgue
and then buried.

05:51.921 --> 05:53.937
[hums]
You can't fake that.

05:54.065 --> 05:55.953
Let's check out the kitchen.

06:04.049 --> 06:05.649
Ooh.

06:05.777 --> 06:07.633
Oh, this is where Sidney
and Gale Weathers

06:07.761 --> 06:09.841
roasted Amber Freeman
a few years ago.

06:09.968 --> 06:12.145
Yeah, where
she was torched. [sighs]

06:12.273 --> 06:14.417
I would hate to die that way.

06:22.417 --> 06:23.313
[gasps]

06:23.440 --> 06:24.593
Oh, my God.
It's fake.

06:24.721 --> 06:25.969
It's fake. [chuckles]

06:26.097 --> 06:27.601
Fucking hilarious.

06:28.081 --> 06:29.553
[phone rings]

06:30.353 --> 06:32.241
It's happening.

06:33.393 --> 06:35.345
[line beeps]
Hello?

06:35.473 --> 06:37.969
[voice on phone]
<i>Hello, Scott. Hello, Madison.</i>

06:38.097 --> 06:40.273
<i>Welcome to</i>
<i>the Macher House Experience.</i>

06:40.401 --> 06:41.809
<i>Enjoying it so far?</i>

06:41.937 --> 06:43.217
It's amazing.
Mm-hmm.

06:43.345 --> 06:45.361
<i>Do you like scary movies?</i>

06:45.488 --> 06:46.737
Go, go.

06:46.865 --> 06:48.849
Uh, yeah, my boyfriend's
a big horror fan.

06:48.977 --> 06:50.769
<i>What's your favorite</i>
<i>scary movie?</i>

06:50.897 --> 06:53.265
<i>Stab One.</i>
<i>It's time to play a game.</i>

06:53.393 --> 06:55.569
<i>Scary Movie Trivia.</i>
<i>Three questions.</i>

06:55.697 --> 06:58.833
<i>Get one wrong, and you die.</i>
<i>Question one:</i>

06:58.960 --> 07:01.169
<i>In the original</i>
A Nightmare on Elm Street,

07:01.297 --> 07:03.569
<i>who is the first person</i>
<i>to die?</i>

07:03.697 --> 07:05.265
Tina Gray.
<i>Correct.</i>

07:05.393 --> 07:06.577
<i>Question two:</i>

07:06.705 --> 07:08.177
<i>In</i> The People
Under the Stairs,

07:08.305 --> 07:10.609
<i>what's the name of</i>
<i>Mommy and Daddy's daughter?</i>

07:10.737 --> 07:12.368
Alice.
<i>Very good.</i>

07:12.497 --> 07:14.257
<i>Let's try a hard one</i>
<i>this time.</i>

07:14.385 --> 07:15.505
<i>In</i> Friday the 13th,

07:15.633 --> 07:18.769
<i>how old was Jason Voorhees</i>
<i>when he drowned?</i>

07:19.505 --> 07:21.521
Okay, well,
in <i>The Final Chapter</i>

07:21.649 --> 07:25.169
we found out Mrs. Voorhees
gave birth in 1946, right?

07:25.297 --> 07:29.105
And then in the original,
the two counselors died
in the flashback in '58.

07:29.233 --> 07:31.729
Jason drowned the summer
before that. That's '57.

07:31.857 --> 07:35.185
So born in '46,
drowned in '57.

07:35.729 --> 07:37.617
Eleven. Jason was eleven.

07:37.745 --> 07:41.809
<i>Oh, I'm so sorry, Scott,</i>
<i>but that's incorrect.</i>

07:42.609 --> 07:45.169
Bullshit.
No, the math was right.

07:45.297 --> 07:47.793
It's a trick question.
Jason never drowned.

07:47.921 --> 07:49.841
<i>Very impressive, Madison.</i>

07:49.969 --> 07:52.145
<i>Scott's lucky he has you</i>
<i>to lean on.</i>

07:52.273 --> 07:56.177
<i>I guess I don't get to stab</i>
<i>you guys after all.</i> [chuckles]

07:56.305 --> 07:57.488
<i>You two have a chilling night.</i>

07:57.617 --> 07:59.921
<i>And don't forget to give us</i>
<i>a five-star--</i>

08:00.977 --> 08:01.937
Are you miserable?

08:02.065 --> 08:03.409
I wish I could fake it better.

08:03.537 --> 08:04.593
Why'd you come here
with me?

08:04.721 --> 08:06.673
Well, you were
pushy about it!

08:06.801 --> 08:11.089
And I thought I could be cool,
then we got here
and it's so cheesy.

08:11.217 --> 08:12.401
You want to go?

08:12.529 --> 08:13.777
I don't want to be here
if you don't.

08:13.905 --> 08:15.057
I can drive home right now.

08:15.185 --> 08:16.273
You would drive home
right now?

08:16.401 --> 08:17.457
I would.

08:17.905 --> 08:20.049
No, it's too late.

08:21.105 --> 08:21.937
I'm sorry.

08:22.065 --> 08:24.689
I'm gonna try harder.
I promise.

08:28.369 --> 08:30.193
Okay, now I have to pee.

08:30.321 --> 08:32.081
It's the hallway
on the left.
[chuckles]

08:35.633 --> 08:37.649
[exhales, smacks lips]

08:37.778 --> 08:39.185
[sighs]

08:39.729 --> 08:41.105
[phone rings]

08:46.385 --> 08:47.601
Hello?

08:47.729 --> 08:50.417
[caller] <i>You're going to</i>
<i>die tonight.</i>

08:51.281 --> 08:52.945
Scott, why are you calling me?

08:53.073 --> 08:55.217
[caller] <i>It's not Scott.</i>

08:55.889 --> 08:57.457
Okay.

08:58.513 --> 08:59.537
Who is it then?

08:59.665 --> 09:02.353
[caller] <i>The person</i>
<i>who's gonna kill you.</i>

09:02.481 --> 09:05.009
The scary voice thing is
a little bit sexy,

09:05.137 --> 09:06.641
but you could work on it.

09:06.769 --> 09:08.241
[caller]
<i>Listen, you little bitch,</i>

09:08.369 --> 09:11.313
<i>I'm gonna slice you open</i>
<i>and rip your guts out!</i>

09:11.441 --> 09:13.361
Did you just call me a bitch?

09:13.489 --> 09:16.689
Okay, I said I would try,
but I'm done. This isn't fun.

09:16.817 --> 09:19.889
[caller] <i>Because the fun part</i>
<i>is over, Madison.</i>

09:20.018 --> 09:21.329
[line beeps]

09:21.906 --> 09:23.185
[object thuds]

09:27.825 --> 09:29.201
Scott?

09:30.961 --> 09:33.745
<i>They'd never make it</i>
<i>in time.</i>

09:43.825 --> 09:44.785
Scott!

09:44.914 --> 09:47.441
<i>We're not finished yet.</i>

09:58.289 --> 09:59.729
Fuck you!

10:00.081 --> 10:00.977
Stu--

10:01.105 --> 10:03.057
[gasps, screams]

10:03.537 --> 10:05.521
[Scott groans] Ow! Ow!

10:05.649 --> 10:08.369
It's me.
What the fuck?

10:08.497 --> 10:10.705
[groans] You hit me.
What is wrong with you?

10:10.834 --> 10:12.017
I'm sorry. I thought it...

10:12.145 --> 10:13.521
[panting]
[gasps]

10:13.649 --> 10:15.377
You said you were gonna try.
[stutters] It was a bad idea.

10:15.505 --> 10:18.385
Yeah, of course it was
a bad fucking idea!

10:20.369 --> 10:21.649
It moved.

10:21.777 --> 10:23.314
Yeah, it's electric.
That's what it does.

10:23.441 --> 10:26.417
No. Like, it moved

10:26.929 --> 10:28.369
differently.

10:29.265 --> 10:30.865
[Madison] What?

10:30.994 --> 10:32.914
Oh!
[Madison screams]

10:33.041 --> 10:35.121
[Scott grunts, groans]

10:36.913 --> 10:38.353
[gasps] No!

10:38.481 --> 10:41.201
[screams, sobs]

10:45.041 --> 10:46.673
[screams]

10:50.929 --> 10:51.921
[panting]

10:54.577 --> 10:56.337
[screaming]

10:59.505 --> 11:00.881
[panting]

11:02.642 --> 11:03.825
[screams]

11:10.737 --> 11:12.625
Fuck you! [screams]

11:13.105 --> 11:14.609
[grunts]

11:15.313 --> 11:17.265
[dramatic music playing]

11:29.137 --> 11:30.769
[screams]

11:31.921 --> 11:34.033
[grunting, breathing heavily]

11:40.369 --> 11:42.193
[screams, pants]

11:48.881 --> 11:51.377
[screams]

11:51.506 --> 11:52.753
[flesh squelches]

11:54.641 --> 11:56.721
[grunting, panting]

11:58.609 --> 12:00.210
[groans]

12:00.338 --> 12:01.873
[quiet, high-pitched ringing]

12:10.129 --> 12:11.473
[clattering]

12:20.498 --> 12:22.129
[muttering weakly]

12:25.106 --> 12:26.577
[flames roar]

12:30.481 --> 12:32.465
[whimpering, groaning]

12:32.593 --> 12:36.849
No! No, no, no. No, no, no.
[cries]

12:37.329 --> 12:38.449
[sobbing]

12:39.409 --> 12:42.065
[screaming]

12:47.601 --> 12:48.945
[glass shatters]

12:50.002 --> 12:51.986
[dramatic music playing]

13:07.857 --> 13:09.841
[phone ringing]

13:11.633 --> 13:13.393
[screaming]

13:14.321 --> 13:16.465
["Criminal" playing]

13:19.153 --> 13:21.009
[typing]

13:22.929 --> 13:24.594
[phone chimes]

13:33.298 --> 13:34.577
[crunching]

13:36.017 --> 13:38.034
[ominous music plays]

13:49.650 --> 13:50.642
[screams]

13:50.769 --> 13:51.985
Jesus, you scared me.

13:52.113 --> 13:53.937
You're gonna give me
a heart attack.

13:54.065 --> 13:56.785
I'm sorry.
What are you doing here?

13:57.298 --> 13:58.481
Well...

14:00.497 --> 14:03.825
it occurred to me
that I've never snuck through
your bedroom window.

14:04.369 --> 14:06.641
I was home, bored,

14:07.890 --> 14:08.786
watching TV...

14:08.914 --> 14:10.097
Mmm.

14:13.041 --> 14:14.706
...and <i>Stab</i> was on.

14:15.410 --> 14:17.330
And that just got me
thinking of you.

14:17.458 --> 14:18.801
That's horrific.

14:18.929 --> 14:20.625
Billy snuck through
Sidney's window, so...

14:20.753 --> 14:23.218
Mm-hmm.
I'm well aware.

14:23.346 --> 14:25.298
You know,
if my mom catches you...

14:25.425 --> 14:27.858
Mmm. Just a kiss.

14:37.522 --> 14:38.418
Hey.

14:38.546 --> 14:39.825
Hi.

14:45.713 --> 14:46.833
[knocking on door]
[boyfriend] Oh!

14:46.961 --> 14:48.242
[body thuds]

14:48.369 --> 14:49.713
[door opens]

14:50.258 --> 14:51.729
Can you knock?

14:51.858 --> 14:53.169
I did.

14:53.297 --> 14:54.641
Can you wait for a response?

14:55.153 --> 14:56.337
Something wrong?

14:56.754 --> 14:57.906
No.

14:58.033 --> 14:59.538
No, everything's fine.
You sure?

14:59.666 --> 15:00.530
Mm-hmm.

15:00.658 --> 15:02.450
Ben, how you doing over there?

15:02.578 --> 15:05.809
On the floor. Behind the bed.

15:06.354 --> 15:08.849
Hello, Mrs. Evans.

15:08.977 --> 15:10.418
How are you this evening?

15:10.545 --> 15:13.138
Oh, well, I'm tired.
Ben, it's late.

15:13.266 --> 15:16.593
That's why I didn't want to
disturb anyone by...

15:16.721 --> 15:17.906
using the door.

15:18.034 --> 15:19.569
So thoughtful.

15:20.594 --> 15:21.297
Out.

15:21.425 --> 15:22.929
But he's here now.
No.

15:23.057 --> 15:24.945
That's okay. I'm going.

15:29.362 --> 15:31.025
Good night, Tate.

15:35.761 --> 15:38.609
[Ben] I know it's late.
I'm sorry, Mrs. Evans.

15:38.737 --> 15:41.553
That was on me.
Tatum had no idea
that I was coming over.

15:41.682 --> 15:44.786
Okay, well,
let's not do it again.

15:47.345 --> 15:48.369
[sighs]

15:51.666 --> 15:53.137
I'm a good guy, Mrs. Evans.

15:53.266 --> 15:54.641
Good night, Ben.

16:05.010 --> 16:06.417
Hypocrite.

16:09.009 --> 16:10.450
[scoffs]

16:13.458 --> 16:16.049
It's not like a boy's never
crawled through your window.

16:16.177 --> 16:18.065
[phone chimes]
We've all seen the movie.

16:18.194 --> 16:20.561
Which is why it's never
gonna happen in this house.

16:20.689 --> 16:22.673
Why do you not like him?

16:23.346 --> 16:24.465
[sighs]

16:24.593 --> 16:25.713
I don't not like him.

16:25.842 --> 16:27.537
I just--
I want you to be smart.

16:27.665 --> 16:29.457
And not trust him so easily.

16:29.585 --> 16:30.770
We're not having sex,

16:30.898 --> 16:32.690
if that's
what you're worried about.

16:33.137 --> 16:34.706
I mean, we want to,

16:35.858 --> 16:37.394
but I don't think we're ready.

16:37.522 --> 16:40.530
Well, if you're asking
the question, then, um...

16:41.105 --> 16:42.705
you're probably not.

16:42.833 --> 16:44.274
How did you know?

16:47.697 --> 16:50.194
I mean,
did that really happen to you?

16:50.353 --> 16:51.505
Like in the movie?

16:54.225 --> 16:56.177
It's freezing in here.

16:56.978 --> 16:58.353
[Sidney exhales]

17:02.161 --> 17:03.698
How about we have
these kinds of conversations

17:03.825 --> 17:05.681
during waking hours, okay?

17:05.809 --> 17:09.042
No more boys in windows,
please.

17:10.002 --> 17:10.994
[Sidney sighs]

17:12.721 --> 17:13.778
Night.

17:15.633 --> 17:17.618
[sighs]

17:23.217 --> 17:24.594
How ugly did it get?

17:26.226 --> 17:27.793
I was extremely polite.

17:27.921 --> 17:29.649
You know,
she's not the first girl

17:29.777 --> 17:31.282
to let a boy
sneak in her window.

17:31.410 --> 17:33.489
Yeah. She made that point.

17:33.617 --> 17:35.122
You know, if being
an overprotective mom

17:35.250 --> 17:37.393
is the worst thing she can
say about me... [sighs]

17:37.521 --> 17:39.154
...I think I can
live with that.

17:39.281 --> 17:40.594
You think they're doing it?

17:40.722 --> 17:42.898
Oh, God, no.

17:43.026 --> 17:45.426
[chuckles] No. Not yet.

17:45.554 --> 17:47.985
But I think we've got
about five minutes left.

17:49.137 --> 17:51.057
How old were you
when you started?

17:51.186 --> 17:53.106
Same age as you. Seventeen.

17:53.234 --> 17:56.242
Oh, did I say seventeen?
I think I meant fifteen.

17:57.745 --> 17:58.866
Did you lie to me?

17:58.994 --> 18:01.746
Look, in my defense,
I don't remember.

18:01.874 --> 18:03.922
Oh, you don't remember
the first time you had sex?

18:04.050 --> 18:06.066
Oh, no, I don't remember
what I told you.

18:06.193 --> 18:08.177
Oh, you told me seventeen.

18:08.305 --> 18:11.089
Look, I didn't want to
come off as, you know...

18:11.217 --> 18:12.945
Uh-huh. Keep going.
I want to see where this goes.

18:13.073 --> 18:14.993
[stammers] I just wanted you
to see me

18:15.122 --> 18:16.817
as more than a sex slave.

18:16.945 --> 18:19.825
Oh. You have a mind, too?

18:19.954 --> 18:22.034
You know... well, yeah.

18:22.162 --> 18:24.114
[gentle music playing]

18:32.690 --> 18:34.642
[people chuckling]

18:34.770 --> 18:36.881
[rock music playing]

18:37.009 --> 18:38.929
[saw whirring]

18:39.057 --> 18:40.402
[people chattering
indistinctly]

18:42.450 --> 18:43.697
[contractor] Morning, Chief.

18:43.825 --> 18:45.298
Hey, Woody. Look at that,
the walls are up, right?

18:45.426 --> 18:46.994
Looks great.

18:47.122 --> 18:49.010
[child on tablet] <i>Love you.</i>
I love you, too.
We miss you guys.

18:49.138 --> 18:50.930
[Mark]
Construction's coming along.
<i>We're keeping them busy.</i>

18:51.058 --> 18:52.914
Oh. Hey, Mom.
[mother] <i>Hi there, baby.</i>

18:53.042 --> 18:56.081
[child] <i>Hi, Daddy.</i>
Thanks, Junie.
I'm glad you're having fun.

18:56.209 --> 18:57.682
If you need anything, call.
<i>Okay.</i>

18:57.810 --> 19:00.049
I love you. Thank you
for watching the maniacs.

19:00.177 --> 19:01.618
We'll see you this weekend.

19:01.746 --> 19:02.546
<i>Bye.</i>
Bye.

19:02.674 --> 19:03.538
[tablet chimes]

19:03.666 --> 19:05.905
She's very brave.
Yep.

19:08.689 --> 19:10.898
[ominous music plays]
[saw whirs]

19:12.497 --> 19:13.682
What?

19:14.417 --> 19:16.018
Where'd you find that?

19:16.146 --> 19:17.425
Um, the attic.

19:17.554 --> 19:19.313
I was looking through
some old clothes.

19:22.097 --> 19:23.698
Do you not want me to wear it?

19:23.826 --> 19:25.234
You could have asked.

19:27.729 --> 19:29.330
Honey, maybe take it off.

19:35.665 --> 19:37.714
What age
do they get nice again?

19:39.281 --> 19:40.722
That was on you.

19:42.418 --> 19:44.049
[inhales deeply]

19:44.498 --> 19:46.354
[sighs]

19:48.881 --> 19:50.450
[mysterious music plays]

19:51.474 --> 19:52.849
[sighs]

19:55.761 --> 19:57.681
You can wear the jacket.

19:58.354 --> 19:59.666
It's okay, I'm good.

20:00.082 --> 20:01.618
Tatum, I'm sorry.

20:01.746 --> 20:03.154
Okay? It caught me off guard.

20:03.281 --> 20:04.530
I hadn't seen it
since college.

20:04.658 --> 20:06.546
I thought I'd gotten rid
of it.

20:06.674 --> 20:09.266
Yeah, the mysterious
one semester at Windsor
we can't talk about.

20:09.394 --> 20:10.578
That's not true.

20:10.706 --> 20:12.881
Really? Since when?

20:13.009 --> 20:15.250
Your childhood is
completely off-limits.

20:15.378 --> 20:18.130
[laughs]
What are you talking about?
It's not off-limits.

20:18.258 --> 20:19.986
It's online and in movies
and in books.

20:20.114 --> 20:21.810
You could do a deep dive
whenever you want.

20:21.938 --> 20:23.794
As long as
I don't ask questions.

20:27.281 --> 20:29.297
You have rehearsal today?

20:30.610 --> 20:31.602
Yep.

20:33.041 --> 20:34.482
How's it going?

20:36.913 --> 20:38.066
Horrible.

20:38.610 --> 20:40.338
Tragic. [chuckles]

20:40.466 --> 20:42.962
I get so nervous onstage,
it's painful to watch.

20:43.090 --> 20:46.641
Oh, God! I used to
get stage fright.
I know the feeling.

20:47.218 --> 20:48.946
You did theater?

20:50.866 --> 20:52.305
Not since college.

20:53.874 --> 20:57.426
Anyway, don't worry.
You're gonna do great.

20:59.089 --> 21:00.849
I got to get to work.

21:05.522 --> 21:07.090
Fucking motherhood.

21:07.218 --> 21:08.689
Great talk.

21:08.818 --> 21:10.962
["The Kill" playing]

21:34.898 --> 21:38.002
["The Kill" continues
through speakers]

21:39.954 --> 21:41.522
Morning.
Hey, morning.

21:46.834 --> 21:48.306
[server] We'll have that
right out for you. Okay?

21:48.434 --> 21:49.905
[customer]
All right. Thank you.

21:50.034 --> 21:52.178
Busy?
Little AM rush,
but not too bad.

21:52.306 --> 21:53.106
Good. [sighs]

21:53.234 --> 21:55.601
Hey, Mrs. Evans.
Hey, Lucas.

21:55.730 --> 21:57.585
Oh, could I get
four espresso shots, please?

21:57.714 --> 21:58.610
Yeah. For sure.

21:58.738 --> 22:00.882
Four?
Yeah. [chuckles]

22:01.010 --> 22:03.249
Rehearsal today.
It's gonna be a long one.

22:03.377 --> 22:04.850
What part do you play?

22:04.978 --> 22:06.002
Oh, just a techie. Yeah.

22:06.129 --> 22:08.402
I work the, uh--
the lighting board.

22:08.530 --> 22:10.418
Cool.
Yeah. [inhales sharply]

22:10.546 --> 22:11.921
Hey, an old <i>Dateline</i>
was on last night

22:12.050 --> 22:13.170
about the Ghostface Killers
in New York.

22:13.298 --> 22:14.610
Have you, uh--
Have you seen it?

22:14.738 --> 22:16.658
No, I haven't.

22:16.785 --> 22:19.186
It's not as good as the
Netflix doc, but it's decent.

22:19.314 --> 22:21.266
They did a good job
covering the aftermath.

22:21.394 --> 22:22.962
[sighs] Morning.

22:23.090 --> 22:24.146
Hey.

22:24.274 --> 22:25.361
Did you say anything?
Mm-mmm.

22:25.490 --> 22:26.546
Did he ask you about <i>Dateline?</i>

22:26.674 --> 22:27.922
It's fine, really.

22:28.050 --> 22:29.297
No, it isn't.

22:29.426 --> 22:30.674
I told you not to.
Ow!

22:30.802 --> 22:32.049
That hurt.
Good.

22:32.177 --> 22:35.378
I'm a crime junkie, Mom.
It's my-- It's my thing.

22:35.506 --> 22:37.841
[sighs] I'm sorry, Mrs. Evans.

22:37.970 --> 22:39.890
But I really want to
start a podcast,

22:40.018 --> 22:40.914
and I think
the New York murders

22:41.042 --> 22:42.226
would be a primo first case.

22:42.354 --> 22:44.593
Don't you have
rehearsal now, honey?

22:44.722 --> 22:45.842
Right?
Yes.

22:45.970 --> 22:48.210
So you should leave now.
Right. Yeah. Okay.

22:48.338 --> 22:49.714
Okay. Great.
Bye.

22:49.842 --> 22:50.706
Bye.
Bye!

22:50.834 --> 22:53.650
[sighs] I'm sorry.
It's fine.

22:54.193 --> 22:55.314
What'll you have?

22:55.442 --> 22:57.586
["The Kill" continues]

23:01.010 --> 23:02.738
["The Kill" continues
through earbuds]

23:02.866 --> 23:04.626
[Tatum] Hey, wait up!

23:04.754 --> 23:05.938
[friend] Oh, hey.
[friend 2] Hi!

23:06.066 --> 23:08.114
You look hot.
Where'd you get the jacket?

23:08.242 --> 23:10.418
Thanks. It's my mom's.
'90s vintage.

23:10.546 --> 23:11.826
[gasps]
You should bedazzle it.

23:11.954 --> 23:12.658
Yes.

23:12.786 --> 23:14.642
Oh! Tonight,
my place, party.

23:14.770 --> 23:16.241
I've been stockpiling
my mom's edibles.

23:16.370 --> 23:18.226
And you can even
invite creepy boy.

23:18.354 --> 23:19.890
Listen, he's not creepy.

23:20.018 --> 23:21.234
Mmm.
He's deep.

23:21.362 --> 23:22.866
And he has a squeezy butt.
Ew.

23:22.994 --> 23:25.650
The true crime is cringy.
He's obsessed with my mom.

23:25.778 --> 23:27.986
Is your mom gonna let you out
of your cage tonight?

23:28.114 --> 23:29.938
I-- [sighs] I don't know.

23:30.066 --> 23:33.202
Honestly,
she's been on overdrive
with the mama trauma.

23:33.330 --> 23:36.530
Well, if anyone has a right
to be insane, it is your mom.

23:36.658 --> 23:38.162
Very true. I've seen
all the <i>Stab</i> movies.

23:38.289 --> 23:40.722
Personally, I don't know how
she's not in a psych ward.

23:40.850 --> 23:41.746
[horn honks]

23:41.874 --> 23:42.770
Oh.
Oh.

23:42.898 --> 23:44.722
Look who it is.
[Ben] Hey!

23:44.850 --> 23:48.050
Top of the morning!
Hey, Tay.

23:48.178 --> 23:49.298
Hey, babe.
Hiya.

23:49.426 --> 23:50.866
You all need a lift?

23:50.994 --> 23:52.754
You guys, come on!
Yes!

23:52.882 --> 23:55.730
We don't have to walk anymore.
Let's go!
Yeah, yeah, yeah. Buckle up.

23:55.858 --> 23:57.522
[pop punk music playing]

23:57.650 --> 23:59.634
Buckle up. Buckle up!

24:00.338 --> 24:01.874
[teenagers laugh]

24:02.290 --> 24:03.377
Karl!

24:12.370 --> 24:14.002
Thank you.

24:14.674 --> 24:16.914
I am so sorry about Lucas.
No.

24:17.042 --> 24:19.314
It's just you're like
a celebrity to him.

24:21.202 --> 24:23.186
You feel like
you guys are close, right?

24:23.314 --> 24:27.122
Yeah. I mean, I suppose
we've had to be
since it's just the two of us.

24:27.250 --> 24:31.058
Do you ever talk to him about
your life before you had him?

24:31.186 --> 24:32.370
No.
No?

24:32.498 --> 24:34.354
No, no. I mean,
there's not much I can say

24:34.482 --> 24:36.242
about his abusive
asshole father

24:36.370 --> 24:39.314
and how badly our marriage
fucked me up.

24:39.442 --> 24:40.978
Why? What's going on?

24:41.106 --> 24:43.090
Oh, I don't know. Uh...

24:43.218 --> 24:45.778
Tatum and I are having
a bit of a rough patch.

24:45.906 --> 24:48.722
She's at that age where she
wants to know about my past.

24:48.850 --> 24:50.770
And as you know, my past
is full of dead people.

24:50.898 --> 24:53.650
Not exactly something
I want to share with her.

24:53.778 --> 24:56.626
So I get quiet,
and then she gets loud,

24:56.754 --> 24:58.290
and around and around we go.

24:58.418 --> 25:00.210
Listen. She's your daughter,

25:00.338 --> 25:02.482
and it's natural
she should want to know you.

25:02.610 --> 25:04.146
You know, I just--
I want my kids to be able

25:04.274 --> 25:06.706
to be who they are
without living in fear.

25:06.834 --> 25:09.074
I want them to feel safe
and protected.

25:09.202 --> 25:10.994
But it's not
a safe world, Sid.

25:11.122 --> 25:12.850
And if we protect
our children too much,

25:12.978 --> 25:15.506
they'll never learn
how to protect themselves.

25:17.970 --> 25:20.914
[performer]
♪ <i>Be not afraid</i>
<i>Don't run away</i> ♪

25:21.042 --> 25:24.242
♪ <i>In here you're safe</i>
<i>Inside your dreamscape</i> ♪

25:24.370 --> 25:26.739
♪ <i>It's meant to be</i>
<i>I come to thee</i> ♪

25:26.866 --> 25:29.362
♪ <i>So will you come with me?</i> ♪

25:29.490 --> 25:31.890
♪ <i>I'll show you</i>
<i>That you're capable</i> ♪

25:32.018 --> 25:35.634
♪ <i>Of knowing things</i>
<i>You've never known</i> ♪

25:35.762 --> 25:38.195
♪ <i>I promise</i>
<i>Life is beautiful</i> ♪

25:38.322 --> 25:40.082
[Tatum] Oh, fuck! [groans]

25:40.210 --> 25:41.682
[performer] ♪ <i>Beautiful</i> ♪

25:42.257 --> 25:43.506
Watch out!

25:43.955 --> 25:46.226
[screams] Oh, fuck!

25:46.867 --> 25:48.434
[chuckles]

25:48.562 --> 25:49.554
[techie] Sorry.

25:49.937 --> 25:50.834
Fuck me.

25:50.962 --> 25:52.338
I'm stuck!

25:52.466 --> 25:53.619
[teacher] No.

25:53.746 --> 25:56.722
No. Uh, houselights, please.

25:56.850 --> 25:58.290
Where's Aaron? Aaron!

25:58.419 --> 25:59.474
I'm here!

25:59.602 --> 26:01.810
I panicked.
I saw Fluffy and freaked.

26:01.938 --> 26:03.538
Are you trying to kill me?
I'm sorry.

26:03.666 --> 26:05.810
[performer] Come, get me out.
Get me out of it.

26:05.938 --> 26:07.955
[groans] I can't see anything
through this.

26:08.082 --> 26:09.042
Wardrobe! Chloe!

26:09.170 --> 26:10.354
Oh! Yep, I'm here.

26:10.482 --> 26:12.434
I'm over here.
I'm here, I'm here!

26:12.562 --> 26:15.506
My foot keeps on getting stuck
in this dumbass pouch
every time.

26:15.635 --> 26:16.882
Okay, diva. Calm down.

26:17.010 --> 26:18.162
Hey, I'm sorry, Hannah.

26:18.290 --> 26:19.602
Oh, no, you're fine.

26:19.730 --> 26:22.546
Trust me, I'm not a real diva.
Just playing the part of one.

26:22.674 --> 26:25.042
But you don't know that.
You stay scared.

26:25.554 --> 26:26.930
Scram!
[Aaron gasps]

26:27.058 --> 26:28.626
Hannah. Hannah, darling.

26:29.458 --> 26:30.418
[Hannah clears throat]

26:30.546 --> 26:32.626
You and Aaron
need to practice.

26:32.754 --> 26:35.634
Uh, Mr. Willis, I missed
my cue. It's my fault.

26:35.763 --> 26:37.874
Tatum... a word.

26:40.850 --> 26:42.226
We need to talk about
your Fluffy.

26:42.354 --> 26:44.690
Yeah, I can't see
through Fluffy's eyes.

26:44.818 --> 26:47.570
It's more than that.
You're very lackluster.

26:48.082 --> 26:49.490
Fluffy needs energy.

26:49.618 --> 26:51.538
Dogs are lively creatures.

26:51.666 --> 26:54.257
You're too timid. Tatum,
where's your confidence?

26:54.386 --> 26:56.979
You need to bring
more strength to this role.

26:57.106 --> 26:58.674
I'll work on that.

27:00.274 --> 27:02.066
You're Sidney Prescott's
daughter.

27:02.194 --> 27:05.362
You need to channel
some of your mother's fire.

27:06.386 --> 27:07.922
I'm surprised really.

27:08.754 --> 27:10.706
I thought you had more grit.

27:12.626 --> 27:14.482
Well, that was rude.

27:14.610 --> 27:18.099
You're playing a dog.
Your only line is "Woof."
It's not that deep.

27:18.226 --> 27:20.146
Hey, fuck him.

27:20.274 --> 27:21.554
Yeah, fuck him.

27:21.682 --> 27:23.186
Ah, don't let Willis
get to you.

27:23.314 --> 27:26.194
Your Fluffy's incredible.
Thanks, guys.

27:26.322 --> 27:27.346
Um...

27:27.474 --> 27:29.394
Okay, I'm--
I'm gonna go take this off.

27:29.874 --> 27:31.697
I'll help you.

27:31.826 --> 27:33.170
Uh, don't forget.
Party tonight.

27:33.299 --> 27:34.546
My place.
All right.

27:34.674 --> 27:35.698
Whoo!
Mmm!

27:35.826 --> 27:37.171
[chuckles]

27:37.299 --> 27:39.059
[Tatum] Ugh.
Get me out of this thing.

27:39.187 --> 27:41.297
[Ben] I got it.
[zipper unzipping]

27:42.099 --> 27:43.282
That's it.

27:43.410 --> 27:45.714
["Nothing's Gonna
Hurt You Baby" playing]

27:46.450 --> 27:47.731
[sighs]

27:47.859 --> 27:49.330
Am I timid?

27:49.458 --> 27:51.154
Oh, don't let that asshole
get to you.

27:51.282 --> 27:53.394
Answer the question.
Be honest.

27:54.130 --> 27:56.562
I wouldn't say timid, no, but

27:56.690 --> 28:00.146
you have
this really cute shy quality.

28:02.259 --> 28:04.850
"Shy" means "timid," FYI.

28:08.370 --> 28:10.130
Do you think
I lack confidence?

28:10.258 --> 28:13.010
[chuckles] I can't win this.
I'm not playing.

28:13.138 --> 28:14.386
[Tatum mutters, scoffs]

28:15.250 --> 28:18.002
Why do you like me?
That's a really long list.

28:18.130 --> 28:21.106
Okay.
Well, be specific. One thing.

28:23.698 --> 28:26.674
[sighs] No.
It's-- It's cheesy.

28:30.226 --> 28:32.050
Say it anyway.

28:33.362 --> 28:35.026
Okay.

28:37.074 --> 28:39.890
I like how you look at me
in a certain way.

28:40.018 --> 28:41.138
And it makes me smile.

28:41.266 --> 28:44.210
Or you say something
that makes me laugh,

28:45.331 --> 28:46.898
and I'll go home
and I'll think about it later

28:47.026 --> 28:49.714
and I'll smile
and laugh all over again.

28:51.410 --> 28:53.362
I really like that.

28:59.506 --> 29:02.354
That wasn't cheesy.
That was a great answer.

29:02.483 --> 29:05.074
["Nothing's Gonna
Hurt You Baby" continues]

29:12.914 --> 29:14.386
[phone rings]

29:17.330 --> 29:19.955
Hello.
[caller] <i>Hello, Sidney.</i>

29:20.082 --> 29:23.250
<i>Guess who. Did you miss me?</i>

29:23.378 --> 29:26.034
<i>I see you found</i>
<i>a new town to live in.</i>

29:26.162 --> 29:27.986
<i>It reminds me a lot of</i>
<i>where we grew up.</i>

29:28.114 --> 29:29.587
Oh, do we know each other?

29:29.714 --> 29:30.994
[caller] <i>We sure do.</i>

29:31.122 --> 29:33.490
<i>In fact, I was just</i>
<i>in Woodsboro last night.</i>

29:33.617 --> 29:35.922
<i>Things got a little... heated.</i>

29:36.051 --> 29:38.386
<i>But I'm here</i>
<i>in Pine Grove now.</i>

29:38.514 --> 29:40.019
Yeah? What brings you here?

29:40.147 --> 29:41.618
[caller] <i>You, Sidney.</i>

29:41.746 --> 29:45.394
<i>You were missed in New York.</i>
<i>It's not the same without you.</i>

29:45.522 --> 29:47.890
<i>I guess you couldn't</i>
<i>be bothered now that you're</i>

29:48.017 --> 29:50.834
<i>so busy with a husband</i>
<i>and family.</i>

29:50.962 --> 29:52.499
Well, you sure know
a lot about me

29:52.627 --> 29:54.002
for another asshole
hiding behind

29:54.130 --> 29:55.570
a fake number
and a voice changer.

29:55.697 --> 29:59.794
[caller] <i>Oh, I'm not hiding,</i>
<i>Sidney. Not this time.</i>

29:59.922 --> 30:01.906
[phone chiming]

30:03.794 --> 30:05.394
[inhales shakily]

30:08.050 --> 30:10.226
<i>Surprise, Sidney.</i>

30:12.082 --> 30:13.523
<i>Do you need a minute? Oh!</i>
<i>Oh, my gosh.</i>

30:13.651 --> 30:15.571
<i>It looks like you need</i>
<i>a minute. I'll wait.</i>

30:15.699 --> 30:17.331
[scoffs]

30:17.459 --> 30:19.186
Nice try. Stu Macher is dead.

30:19.315 --> 30:22.738
<i>Oh, gosh.</i>
<i>I'm gonna agree to</i>
<i>disagree with you there.</i>

30:22.866 --> 30:23.858
[chuckles]

30:23.987 --> 30:26.450
<i>Oh, my God!</i>
<i>It is so good to see you.</i>

30:26.578 --> 30:29.107
<i>I always had</i>
<i>a thing for you, Sid!</i>

30:29.234 --> 30:30.194
[giggles]

30:30.322 --> 30:32.210
<i>It's gonna be so much fun.</i>

30:32.338 --> 30:36.274
<i>Just like the old days,</i>
<i>except now there's no Billy</i>
<i>or Randy or Tatum.</i>

30:36.402 --> 30:38.034
<i>Speaking of whom,</i>
<i>your daughter,</i>

30:38.162 --> 30:40.754
<i>her name's Tatum.</i>
<i>That is so adorable.</i>

30:40.882 --> 30:45.554
<i>I mean, It's a little weird or</i>
<i>whatever, but it's supercute.</i>

30:45.682 --> 30:47.762
<i>And she is</i>

30:48.947 --> 30:50.546
<i>so pretty.</i>

30:50.674 --> 30:52.787
Do not talk about my daughter.

30:52.915 --> 30:54.226
<i>Oh. Okay, yeah.</i>

30:54.354 --> 30:55.987
[stutters] <i>I should definitely</i>
<i>tell you, though,</i>

30:56.114 --> 30:59.186
<i>I am currently outside of</i>
<i>her high school theater.</i>

30:59.827 --> 31:01.842
Don't you fucking dare!

31:01.970 --> 31:03.603
<i>It's showtime, bitch.</i>

31:03.730 --> 31:05.777
[dramatic music playing]

31:06.291 --> 31:07.730
Hey, Chief.

31:08.657 --> 31:09.970
You're gonna want to
hear this.

31:10.099 --> 31:11.858
I just got a call from
the police in Woodsboro.

31:11.987 --> 31:13.842
[phone buzzes]
[Mark] Just a sec.

31:13.971 --> 31:14.867
Hey, babe.

31:14.995 --> 31:16.083
[horn honking]

31:16.210 --> 31:17.394
You need to go to the theater
right now.

31:17.522 --> 31:18.835
[Mark] <i>What? What--</i>

31:18.963 --> 31:20.659
There's a killer, Mark.
He's going for Tatum.

31:20.786 --> 31:23.218
I'm on it. All available units
to the high school theater now!

31:23.346 --> 31:25.427
<i>I'm on my way, babe.</i>
Mark, hurry.

31:26.770 --> 31:29.106
[tires squeal]

31:29.619 --> 31:31.155
[siren wailing]

31:37.139 --> 31:38.322
[rattling]

31:44.177 --> 31:45.266
[door opens]

31:45.394 --> 31:47.507
[ominous music plays]

31:53.203 --> 31:55.954
[Hannah] Start with liftoffs
and landings, okay?

31:56.083 --> 31:57.075
[Aaron] Got it.

31:59.506 --> 32:00.594
Ready?

32:00.722 --> 32:01.811
Ready.

32:05.394 --> 32:07.731
[grunts] Okay, a little hard
on the landing there.

32:07.859 --> 32:09.106
[Aaron] Sorry.

32:10.930 --> 32:12.755
It's just too jerky.

32:12.882 --> 32:14.546
Softer.
Got it.

32:16.914 --> 32:18.898
[clang in distance]
Huh?

32:19.026 --> 32:20.626
[Hannah] Try it again.

32:22.834 --> 32:24.851
Okay, any day now!
Oh.

32:28.594 --> 32:30.450
[slash]
[Aaron groans]

32:30.578 --> 32:31.795
Hey, Aaron?

32:31.923 --> 32:33.491
[thud]

32:36.691 --> 32:37.874
Hello?

32:40.754 --> 32:43.666
[scoffs]
This is my nice voice.

32:45.586 --> 32:46.931
[exclaims]

32:50.290 --> 32:51.666
Aaron?

33:00.531 --> 33:01.555
Shit.

33:04.114 --> 33:07.123
Aaron? I want to get down now.

33:07.251 --> 33:08.722
[grunting]

33:09.617 --> 33:10.867
Shit.

33:11.762 --> 33:12.883
Hello!

33:13.394 --> 33:17.362
[door opens, closes]

33:19.059 --> 33:21.298
No! No!

33:21.907 --> 33:23.666
[grunts, panting]

33:29.906 --> 33:32.083
Put me down-- [screams]

33:33.971 --> 33:35.602
[panting]

33:37.299 --> 33:38.259
This isn't funny--

33:38.386 --> 33:39.795
[screams]

33:41.875 --> 33:42.835
Aaron!

33:42.963 --> 33:44.338
[grunting, panting]

33:48.339 --> 33:49.459
Aaron!

33:54.386 --> 33:55.379
Aaron!

33:55.507 --> 33:57.586
No! [screams]

33:58.003 --> 33:59.123
Help!

34:00.051 --> 34:01.011
Get me out!

34:01.139 --> 34:02.899
[screams] This hurts!

34:03.026 --> 34:03.923
Aaron!

34:04.051 --> 34:05.811
Hello!

34:05.939 --> 34:08.467
[grunting, panting]

34:10.706 --> 34:13.267
What the fuck?

34:14.002 --> 34:15.411
[screaming]

34:15.539 --> 34:16.722
No, wait!

34:18.706 --> 34:20.243
Shit!

34:20.754 --> 34:22.067
Oh, my God, please!

34:22.195 --> 34:23.634
[screams] No, wait!

34:23.763 --> 34:25.971
Hey, you stay away from me!

34:27.314 --> 34:28.659
Get away!

34:30.354 --> 34:32.563
No, please, wait! [screams]

34:34.066 --> 34:35.890
[screaming, crying]

34:38.066 --> 34:41.043
Please! Please!

34:43.475 --> 34:44.657
Please!

34:47.315 --> 34:50.386
Stop, please! Please, please!

34:50.514 --> 34:52.434
I don't want to die!

34:55.122 --> 34:56.467
[ominous music plays]

34:56.595 --> 34:58.066
[Sidney] Tatum!

35:02.291 --> 35:04.147
Motherfucker!

35:06.737 --> 35:08.883
[dramatic music playing]

35:14.739 --> 35:16.787
Cover the exits!
[guards shouting]

35:16.915 --> 35:18.866
[panting]

35:19.826 --> 35:21.137
Oh, God. Okay.

35:28.690 --> 35:29.939
Tatum!

35:30.737 --> 35:32.115
Mom, what are you doing?
Oh, God!

35:32.243 --> 35:35.091
Are you okay?
Oh, good... okay... okay.

35:35.219 --> 35:37.362
[Sidney panting]

35:44.082 --> 35:46.066
[no audible dialogue]

35:46.194 --> 35:47.763
I wasn't even here.
I had already left.

35:47.890 --> 35:49.107
He was home with me.

35:49.651 --> 35:50.866
Okay. Where were you?

35:52.339 --> 35:53.939
I was downstairs
in the costume shop.

35:54.067 --> 35:56.306
[Ben] Not when
I was there.
Wait, you were here?

35:56.435 --> 35:57.682
No, he left and I was there.

35:57.811 --> 36:00.115
But I didn't see you.

36:00.243 --> 36:02.195
I was in the dressing rooms.

36:02.322 --> 36:03.571
The whole time?

36:04.337 --> 36:07.154
No. Not the whole time.

36:07.282 --> 36:09.619
I went home,
had a light dinner,
Aperol Spritz.

36:09.746 --> 36:12.339
My God, who would do
something like this?

36:12.467 --> 36:14.546
We don't even
have an understudy.

36:14.675 --> 36:17.395
Hey.
Hey.

36:17.523 --> 36:19.507
So, the killer fled.

36:19.634 --> 36:21.811
Whoever did this
knew their way around here.

36:21.939 --> 36:23.987
It was well-thought-out
and executed.

36:24.115 --> 36:25.811
What about the kids?
Did you call your mom?

36:25.939 --> 36:27.187
I called.

36:27.314 --> 36:29.811
The entire Denver police force
is with them, they're safe.

36:31.217 --> 36:32.883
Two teens are dead.

36:33.010 --> 36:34.771
Mark, what the fuck?

36:34.899 --> 36:36.977
[Sidney sniffling]

36:37.107 --> 36:38.483
You are not alone.

36:39.219 --> 36:40.435
We got this.

36:41.331 --> 36:43.795
If this is Stu...
It's not Stu.

36:43.923 --> 36:47.027
It's not.
He is buried in Woodsboro.

36:47.155 --> 36:49.299
Look, we are taking that
phone call that you recorded,

36:49.426 --> 36:50.867
we're sending it
to the state police.

36:50.995 --> 36:53.202
They have the resources
to determine who it is.

36:53.330 --> 36:54.643
We are gonna get him.

36:55.923 --> 36:58.195
Isn't Ben a computer junkie?

36:59.187 --> 37:00.595
[Mark] Aren't all kids?

37:00.723 --> 37:04.083
He applied to Carnegie Mellon
to study computer science.

37:04.211 --> 37:07.315
I hear you.
But anybody can do
deepfakes these days.

37:07.443 --> 37:08.530
[sighs]

37:08.657 --> 37:10.035
Why don't you get Tatum?

37:10.163 --> 37:12.051
Just give me a minute and then
we'll get out of here.

37:16.306 --> 37:17.811
[Sidney]
Tatum, we're going.

37:19.027 --> 37:20.211
Not you.

37:21.074 --> 37:22.611
Mom.
Answer's no.

37:22.739 --> 37:23.699
But, Mrs. Evans--

37:23.827 --> 37:25.011
No.

37:28.019 --> 37:30.067
It's okay.
You go with your family.

37:31.315 --> 37:32.626
I'll call you.

37:39.859 --> 37:41.619
Why do you treat him
like that?

37:42.419 --> 37:43.315
He's not a killer.

37:43.443 --> 37:44.371
You don't know that.

37:44.499 --> 37:47.475
Not everyone is Billy Loomis.

37:47.603 --> 37:49.043
Just because you can't
trust people,

37:49.171 --> 37:51.187
doesn't mean people can't
be trusted.

37:51.891 --> 37:53.171
We're not doing this here.

37:56.914 --> 37:59.059
[suspenseful music playing]

38:07.186 --> 38:09.746
They'll sweep the house.
Yeah. We'll be quick, Chief.

38:30.258 --> 38:31.411
[deputy] All clear.

38:32.178 --> 38:33.331
We're gonna
secure the neighborhood.

38:33.459 --> 38:34.706
Great.
We'll only be a few minutes.

38:34.835 --> 38:36.018
Come on.
Thank you.

38:39.667 --> 38:41.714
Grab your stuff.
You leave in five.

38:42.547 --> 38:44.851
Wait. You're not
coming with us?

38:44.979 --> 38:47.186
It's my job to catch
whoever's doing this.

38:58.002 --> 39:00.819
[ominous music plays]

39:00.947 --> 39:02.483
[music stops]

39:02.611 --> 39:03.539
Where's your go bag?

39:03.667 --> 39:05.587
I unpacked it
a long time ago.

39:05.715 --> 39:07.091
Damn it, Tatum.

39:09.075 --> 39:10.131
[sighs]

39:11.763 --> 39:13.203
So, what? We just run?

39:13.330 --> 39:14.707
[sighs]

39:14.835 --> 39:15.923
Yes, we do.

39:16.051 --> 39:18.451
I thought the great
Sidney Prescott never ran.

39:18.579 --> 39:20.243
With you it's different.

39:20.819 --> 39:22.098
They killed Hannah, Mom.

39:22.227 --> 39:24.787
We can't just leave.
Listen, I know this story,

39:24.915 --> 39:27.154
and if we stay,
more people will die.

39:27.283 --> 39:30.355
I'm sorry, but I'm not gonna
risk you getting hurt.

39:32.019 --> 39:33.203
Why didn't you warn me?

39:33.331 --> 39:34.963
About what?
All of this!

39:35.091 --> 39:37.714
If-If I was ready,
maybe I could have saved her.

39:37.843 --> 39:39.283
Maybe I could have
done something.

39:39.411 --> 39:40.659
If you need anything else,
pack it.

39:40.787 --> 39:42.739
Mom, why can't you just
trust me?

39:42.866 --> 39:45.203
We need to go! Okay?

39:50.643 --> 39:51.987
Here, take these.

39:52.114 --> 39:53.875
Why did you
turn the light out?

39:54.483 --> 39:55.635
I thought you did.

39:57.618 --> 39:59.410
[ominous music playing]

39:59.538 --> 40:00.498
Tatum.

40:00.627 --> 40:01.939
Stay behind me.

40:08.051 --> 40:09.235
[Mark whispering] Tatum.

40:11.314 --> 40:12.307
Tatum.

40:14.771 --> 40:16.179
[panting]

40:19.027 --> 40:20.179
Dad.

40:23.283 --> 40:25.491
Please, leave her alone.

40:28.946 --> 40:30.483
Mark, put the gun down.

40:37.299 --> 40:39.700
[Mark]
Hon, it's gonna be okay.

40:39.827 --> 40:40.947
Just look at me.

40:44.755 --> 40:46.195
[Sidney]
It's me that you want.

40:46.323 --> 40:48.723
You just-- you let her go.

40:53.331 --> 40:54.675
Drop!
[Tatum screams]

40:54.803 --> 40:56.147
[Mark grunts]

40:57.523 --> 40:58.451
[Mark yells]

40:58.963 --> 41:00.595
[grunting]

41:10.323 --> 41:12.403
[grunting]

41:17.043 --> 41:17.971
Mark!
Dad!

41:18.100 --> 41:19.731
[groaning]

41:24.626 --> 41:25.875
Run!

41:28.851 --> 41:30.386
[panting] This way!

41:32.787 --> 41:34.834
[Tatum]
What-What are you doing?

41:36.947 --> 41:38.323
Fuck off!

41:41.683 --> 41:44.115
Where are we?
We're safe in here.

41:50.771 --> 41:52.628
You sure he can't get inside?
Yeah.

41:52.755 --> 41:53.971
What is that?
It's another way out.

41:54.099 --> 41:55.635
I need to get your dad.
You stay here.

41:55.763 --> 41:57.139
No, you can't leave me, Mom!

41:58.226 --> 41:59.155
[thud]
[screams]

41:59.283 --> 42:00.691
Let me go with you, please!

42:00.819 --> 42:02.387
Okay, hurry.

42:09.107 --> 42:10.291
[Tatum groans]

42:13.299 --> 42:14.644
[whispering]
Down to the end. Go.

42:14.771 --> 42:15.955
Okay.

42:17.011 --> 42:18.899
[floorboards creak]

42:21.075 --> 42:22.611
[tapping]

42:24.146 --> 42:25.555
[whispers] Shh.

42:31.091 --> 42:32.307
[tapping]

42:40.723 --> 42:42.099
[tapping]

42:44.404 --> 42:45.266
[gasps]

42:45.618 --> 42:46.995
[screams]

42:47.123 --> 42:48.851
Mom!
This way!

42:50.196 --> 42:51.156
[both gasp, scream]

42:51.283 --> 42:52.723
Mom!
Go, go, go!

42:54.258 --> 42:55.763
[exclaiming, panting]

42:58.931 --> 43:00.147
[screaming]

43:03.154 --> 43:04.147
Okay.

43:05.875 --> 43:08.243
[both panting]

43:12.180 --> 43:13.395
Shh-- [gasps]

43:13.523 --> 43:14.867
[screams]

43:20.178 --> 43:21.235
Go, go, go!

43:29.363 --> 43:30.835
[screams]
Mom!

43:31.698 --> 43:32.851
Go!

43:51.700 --> 43:53.683
[panting] Okay. This way.

44:00.180 --> 44:01.811
[Mark yells]

44:02.228 --> 44:03.859
[grunting]

44:14.803 --> 44:16.019
Get the police! Go!
Mom!

44:16.147 --> 44:18.771
Help! Somebody help us!

44:19.123 --> 44:20.883
[grunting]

44:41.747 --> 44:43.571
Hey, are you okay?
[panting]

44:43.698 --> 44:45.683
Are you okay?
Yeah.

44:45.811 --> 44:47.635
God, I love you.
I love you.

44:47.763 --> 44:49.907
[dramatic music playing]

44:52.851 --> 44:53.972
Did I get him?

44:54.355 --> 44:55.251
You got him!

44:55.379 --> 44:56.948
Chad, get the camera now.

44:57.075 --> 44:58.291
Mindy, set up for a remote.

44:58.419 --> 44:59.987
Ma'am, you need to stay
inside your vehicle.

45:00.115 --> 45:01.971
You need to get out
of my face.

45:02.387 --> 45:03.955
Mom! Dad!

45:06.516 --> 45:07.954
Are you okay?
I'm okay.

45:08.083 --> 45:10.099
Oh, that was horrifying.
That was awesome.

45:10.227 --> 45:12.180
Grab the camera.
We need B-roll of everything.

45:12.308 --> 45:13.811
You have to be ready
at all times.

45:13.939 --> 45:16.180
In my defense,
I wasn't exactly expecting

45:16.307 --> 45:17.876
to be part
of vehicular manslaughter

45:18.004 --> 45:19.251
the second we roll into town,

45:19.379 --> 45:21.171
but next time...
next time I will be prepared.

45:21.299 --> 45:23.475
[Sidney panting]

45:24.564 --> 45:25.907
Hey.

45:27.987 --> 45:30.356
Chief, you gonna be okay?
Put pressure on it.

45:30.484 --> 45:32.147
Just sit still for a minute.

45:35.092 --> 45:36.467
You're bleeding.

45:36.595 --> 45:37.972
Your point?

45:38.100 --> 45:40.403
[emotional music playing]

45:44.852 --> 45:45.812
How's Mark?

45:45.940 --> 45:48.115
It takes a lot
to bring him down.

45:49.843 --> 45:51.540
[sighs]

45:51.668 --> 45:53.427
Gale, he said he was Stu.

45:54.452 --> 45:55.859
I'm sorry. What did you say?

45:56.244 --> 45:57.204
Stu.

46:00.147 --> 46:01.236
Stu Macher?

46:01.363 --> 46:03.411
Dead Stu Macher?

46:05.076 --> 46:06.419
Let's unmask this fucker.

46:06.547 --> 46:09.171
[ominous music playing]

46:09.299 --> 46:10.931
Chief?
Do it.

46:15.347 --> 46:16.532
Who is that?

46:16.660 --> 46:20.212
I don't know, but I saw him
today in the coffee shop.

46:20.340 --> 46:21.779
Are you sure?
Yeah.

46:21.907 --> 46:24.659
[Mindy] Nobody knows the guy?
Okay, that's weird.

46:24.787 --> 46:27.667
That is weird. It's always
someone you know.

46:27.795 --> 46:29.459
[sirens blaring]

46:29.587 --> 46:31.155
[mysterious music playing]

46:31.283 --> 46:32.628
[indistinct police chatter]

46:32.756 --> 46:34.963
[Chad] You want more B-roll?
We could make a whole movie.

46:35.091 --> 46:36.339
[Gale]
I don't know what to say.

46:36.468 --> 46:39.283
I meant to brake
and I hit the gas.

46:45.491 --> 46:46.963
Karl Allen Gibbs.

46:47.092 --> 46:49.363
He escaped from Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital
two weeks ago.

46:49.491 --> 46:50.771
Triple murderer.

46:50.900 --> 46:54.036
Any idea why he'd come after
you or your family?

46:54.163 --> 46:56.307
No.
Thanks, Cooke.

46:56.884 --> 46:58.131
Chief.

46:58.931 --> 47:00.115
[sighs]

47:04.404 --> 47:05.556
Well...

47:05.683 --> 47:07.123
He's not gonna
hurt anyone else.

47:07.252 --> 47:08.819
No.

47:09.811 --> 47:11.187
This was too easy.

47:12.595 --> 47:13.779
There's always more than one.

47:13.908 --> 47:14.803
Sidney,

47:14.932 --> 47:16.627
Stu Macher is dead.

47:17.267 --> 47:19.060
[sighs]

47:19.187 --> 47:21.011
Watch Tatum for a minute.

47:23.411 --> 47:25.748
[reporter 1] Sidney. Sidney!

47:25.875 --> 47:28.276
One question for you, Sidney!

47:28.404 --> 47:29.492
Can we have a word?

47:30.387 --> 47:33.779
Sidney! What's going on?
Over here!

47:34.707 --> 47:35.988
[reporter 2]
Can you tell us anything?

47:36.116 --> 47:38.323
What's happening, Sidney?
What's going on?

47:38.451 --> 47:39.634
Sidney!

47:44.564 --> 47:47.123
The network texted.
They want us to go live.

47:47.251 --> 47:49.971
I'll go get Gale.
No! Don't.

47:50.099 --> 47:51.700
No. No, I'm not doing this.
Yes.

47:51.827 --> 47:53.715
They didn't specify
it had to be Gale.

47:53.843 --> 47:56.531
You'll get us fired!
Do it! Come on!

47:56.658 --> 47:58.611
Fine.
[clears throat]

47:59.475 --> 48:02.674
Three, two, one-- Oh, boy.

48:04.052 --> 48:06.772
You try that again, and I'll
rip both your throats out.

48:06.900 --> 48:07.892
Got it?
Copy that.

48:08.020 --> 48:09.780
We just learned
that Gale Weathers

48:09.908 --> 48:12.947
from the now defunct talk show
<i>Good Morning with</i>
<i>Gale Weathers</i> is in town.

48:13.075 --> 48:14.194
Excuse me, Miss Weathers.

48:14.324 --> 48:16.308
Robbie Rivers, WFPO.
May I ask--

48:16.436 --> 48:18.260
Fuck the fuck off.
Okay.

48:18.387 --> 48:21.076
You two are a familiar sight.
What are you doing in town?

48:21.843 --> 48:22.932
Just passing through.

48:23.060 --> 48:24.340
With Gale Weathers?

48:24.467 --> 48:27.315
And you just happened
to run over
an escaped mental patient

48:27.443 --> 48:29.298
in front
of Sidney Evans's home?

48:29.427 --> 48:31.091
What's really
going on here?

48:31.218 --> 48:32.564
Why don't you
get your own story, Robbie.

48:32.692 --> 48:34.900
Yeah, we're not here
to do it for you.

48:35.796 --> 48:38.803
Come on, give a small-town
reporter his big break!

48:42.420 --> 48:44.787
Hey, Sidney.

48:44.914 --> 48:47.763
I'm so sorry this is happening
again, Mrs. Prescott.

48:48.691 --> 48:50.323
Mrs. Evans, Lucas.

48:50.451 --> 48:52.371
Right, yeah. Uh...

48:52.499 --> 48:53.780
Sorry, that's what I meant.

48:54.514 --> 48:56.147
Lucas, do you know
anything about A.I.?

48:56.275 --> 48:58.452
A.I.? Uh, I refuse.

48:58.580 --> 49:01.171
That is the death
of civilization. [chuckles]

49:01.300 --> 49:03.252
[Jessica]
Why are you asking that?

49:03.987 --> 49:05.300
Just be careful, Jess.

49:05.427 --> 49:06.835
Keep your doors locked.

49:08.404 --> 49:10.611
[Jessica sighs]
Okay, come on, let's go.

49:11.124 --> 49:12.116
[gasps]

49:13.523 --> 49:14.611
Oh, you're Gale Weathers. Hey.

49:14.740 --> 49:16.947
And who are you?
Uh...

49:17.363 --> 49:18.548
I'm Lucas.

49:19.123 --> 49:20.211
What are you doing here?

49:20.339 --> 49:22.484
He's my son,
and we live next door.

49:22.612 --> 49:24.274
We're friends
of the family.
Hmm.

49:24.404 --> 49:25.396
[Lucas] Yeah.

49:26.003 --> 49:27.636
You like horror movies, Lucas?

49:27.763 --> 49:29.588
Yeah, I lo-- I love them.

49:29.715 --> 49:31.347
Especially the <i>Stab</i> movies?

49:31.476 --> 49:32.691
Yeah,
I know them inside and out.

49:32.819 --> 49:34.707
What are you doing?
Mom, it's Gale Weathers.

49:34.834 --> 49:37.940
The <i>Stab</i> movies were based
on her true crime bestseller,
<i>The Woodsboro Murders.</i>

49:38.067 --> 49:40.595
I know, but I don't like
the way she's looking at you.

49:40.724 --> 49:44.115
Please leave my son out of
whatever it is you're doing.

49:45.075 --> 49:46.067
Sorry, kid,

49:46.195 --> 49:47.700
but you know how this works.

49:47.828 --> 49:48.724
Yeah.

49:48.851 --> 49:50.995
Everyone's a suspect.

49:51.123 --> 49:54.452
Well, yeah, but you killed
the killer. He's dead.

49:54.580 --> 49:55.763
Hmm.

49:56.787 --> 49:58.803
How do you know
there's just one?

50:00.244 --> 50:01.140
Excuse me.

50:01.268 --> 50:03.220
[scoffs]
Whoa.

50:03.347 --> 50:07.155
Until this is over, I want you
to stay away from this house.

50:07.796 --> 50:09.107
Come on, let's go.

50:14.003 --> 50:15.700
[Sidney]
How did you know to come?

50:15.827 --> 50:18.580
When the news broke
about the two murders
at the Macher house,

50:18.707 --> 50:21.940
a flock of reporters
raced to get there, but...

50:22.068 --> 50:24.435
my Sidney-sense told me
that Woodsboro was played out.

50:24.563 --> 50:28.499
Mark is having
the recorded calls analyzed
to confirm they're fake.

50:28.628 --> 50:30.644
Is it possible
they're real?

50:30.772 --> 50:32.147
Could Stu be alive?

50:32.275 --> 50:36.244
That would be
the better story,
but it's... too far-fetched.

50:36.372 --> 50:37.364
[Gale] Hmm.

50:40.500 --> 50:41.683
What's going on?

50:41.811 --> 50:44.340
Oh, I just have
some nerve damage from the...

50:44.468 --> 50:46.388
from the attack in New York.

50:46.515 --> 50:47.603
You're lucky you sat
that one out.

50:47.732 --> 50:49.587
It-It was brutal.

50:50.228 --> 50:51.188
Thank you.

50:51.315 --> 50:52.564
It's nice to meet you, Tatum.

50:52.692 --> 50:54.419
Mmm. Tatum?

50:55.251 --> 50:56.916
Tatum as in...
That Tatum.

50:57.043 --> 50:58.163
Yeah.

50:58.292 --> 50:59.572
What do you two do for Gale?

50:59.700 --> 51:00.915
We're her hot interns.

51:01.043 --> 51:02.516
Ever since she got axed,

51:02.644 --> 51:04.244
she's been trying to
go back to her roots.

51:04.372 --> 51:07.156
So she's rebranding herself
as a crime reporter.

51:07.284 --> 51:08.755
She's teaching us
all she knows about the biz.

51:08.884 --> 51:10.643
Don't say "biz."
Yep.

51:10.772 --> 51:13.523
It's more like we're showing
Gale the ropes
of making premium content.

51:13.652 --> 51:14.932
Don't say "content."

51:15.060 --> 51:16.371
It's going great.

51:16.500 --> 51:17.555
Except Mindy keeps trying to
steal Gale's thunder.

51:17.684 --> 51:19.700
I'm the face of the future.
Sure.

51:19.827 --> 51:22.548
But in the meantime,
we're learning all about
fading careers

51:22.676 --> 51:24.212
and failed comebacks.

51:25.907 --> 51:27.316
[Gale]
Where are we gonna start?

51:28.115 --> 51:30.835
S-Start what? I'm...

51:32.084 --> 51:33.396
I'm not starting anything.

51:33.523 --> 51:35.795
We have to find out
who's behind this.

51:35.924 --> 51:37.363
That guy in the road,
Karl Gibbs,

51:37.491 --> 51:38.804
is not some random killer.

51:38.932 --> 51:41.395
It's always someone
connected to your past.

51:41.524 --> 51:42.836
The police can handle it.

51:42.964 --> 51:44.211
That would be
your husband.

51:44.340 --> 51:45.684
And we need to help him.

51:46.452 --> 51:48.148
Don't you want to
know who's behind this?

51:48.275 --> 51:50.484
Gale, I can't anymore.

51:50.612 --> 51:53.778
I need to be with my family,
I need to know they're safe.

51:53.908 --> 51:55.060
That's why
you need to help me.

51:55.188 --> 51:57.460
Whoever is targeting you
is not gonna stop...

51:57.587 --> 51:59.156
[phone ringing]
...you know that.

52:03.124 --> 52:06.804
<i>Oh, slap my face, if it</i>
<i>isn't the Gale Weathers!</i>

52:06.932 --> 52:08.083
<i>Hi. Oh, my God,</i>

52:08.211 --> 52:10.163
<i>I am so sorry</i>
<i>your show got canceled</i>

52:10.292 --> 52:11.955
<i>and then you got fired.</i>

52:12.083 --> 52:14.356
I wasn't fired.
My contract wasn't renewed.

52:14.484 --> 52:16.916
<i>So don't care.</i>
<i>Not even a little.</i>

52:17.044 --> 52:19.763
Ugh. I'm so sorry for
running over your friend.

52:19.892 --> 52:21.716
Can't do your own
dirty work, Stu?

52:21.844 --> 52:23.252
[mocking blabbering]

52:23.380 --> 52:24.628
<i>Neither can you.</i>

52:24.755 --> 52:27.860
<i>You brought in some old,</i>
<i>irrelevant hag for backup.</i>

52:27.987 --> 52:29.140
<i>It's so sad.</i>

52:29.267 --> 52:30.484
<i>And what happened to</i>
<i>the two of you?</i>

52:30.612 --> 52:32.243
<i>You both had so much spunk.</i>

52:32.372 --> 52:34.612
You're gonna die,
you A.I. asshole.

52:34.740 --> 52:36.340
<i>We're going to see</i>
<i>how fake I am</i>

52:36.468 --> 52:38.420
<i>when I stab you</i>
<i>in the fucking throat!</i>

52:38.547 --> 52:39.891
<i>Because I'm coming for you</i>

52:40.020 --> 52:43.316
<i>and I'm gonna love</i>
<i>every second of it.</i>

52:43.444 --> 52:44.627
[chuckles]

52:46.451 --> 52:48.020
[sighs]

52:48.147 --> 52:49.876
That was fucking weird.

52:52.628 --> 52:54.356
Fallbrook
Psychiatric Hospital.

52:54.484 --> 52:56.660
It's a couple hours away.
We'll start there.

52:58.131 --> 52:59.315
There she is.

53:00.084 --> 53:01.780
I knew you were
in there somewhere.

53:01.907 --> 53:05.300
You're right. This isn't
gonna stop unless I stop it.

53:12.308 --> 53:13.972
I'll be back as soon as I can.

53:14.100 --> 53:15.956
Mom, I want to go with you.

53:16.084 --> 53:17.876
No, sweetie, it's not safe.

53:18.004 --> 53:18.932
So why are you going?

53:19.060 --> 53:19.956
Because I know what I'm doing.

53:20.083 --> 53:21.236
Mom, please.

53:21.364 --> 53:22.612
You don't have
the skill set for this.

53:22.740 --> 53:24.308
Well, then show me.

53:25.108 --> 53:27.252
I don't want to end up like
the other Tatum.

53:28.500 --> 53:29.683
What?

53:30.484 --> 53:31.540
You named me after a girl who

53:31.667 --> 53:33.972
got her head crushed
in a garage door.

53:34.100 --> 53:36.147
She was my friend.
And she's dead!

53:37.780 --> 53:39.476
She was a-a victim,
not a fighter.

53:39.604 --> 53:41.907
I want to be a fighter.

53:42.036 --> 53:43.508
Honey. Listen--

53:43.636 --> 53:45.332
Nice to know what
you think of me.

53:46.707 --> 53:48.148
[exhales deeply]

53:54.004 --> 53:57.172
She just lost a friend,
so... she's upset.

53:58.132 --> 53:59.764
I want you to keep
her away from Ben.

53:59.892 --> 54:01.908
He's not to come over here.

54:02.036 --> 54:04.820
Someone was hiding
in the attic.
It could have been him.

54:04.947 --> 54:09.236
We are running traces on
all her friends' cell numbers,
emails and IP's.

54:09.364 --> 54:12.532
If Ben or any of her friends
are connected in any way

54:12.660 --> 54:13.843
we're gonna find it.

54:16.948 --> 54:20.372
She's right, you know.
Me protecting her from this,

54:21.012 --> 54:22.740
I made her vulnerable to it.

54:44.052 --> 54:45.044
Right.

54:46.260 --> 54:47.443
Okay.

54:48.244 --> 54:50.836
Okay, Terry. Thanks again.

54:52.916 --> 54:55.924
Woodsboro coroner says
there's no intake form
on Stu Macher's body.

54:56.051 --> 54:59.252
The woman who was coroner
in '96 died three years ago,

54:59.380 --> 55:00.404
so there's no one to ask.

55:00.532 --> 55:03.348
So it's a case
of lost paperwork?

55:03.476 --> 55:04.756
Or stolen paperwork.

55:04.884 --> 55:06.452
Someone who wants to
make it look like Stu's body

55:06.580 --> 55:08.052
never made it to the morgue.

55:09.236 --> 55:10.132
Or...

55:10.260 --> 55:11.476
It's actually Stu.

55:11.604 --> 55:13.459
Let's find out.
Yep.

55:14.291 --> 55:15.572
Here's your pass.
Thank you.

55:16.116 --> 55:17.012
Here you go.

55:17.140 --> 55:18.324
Thanks.

55:19.252 --> 55:20.692
How can I help you?

55:20.820 --> 55:21.971
Hi, I'm Gale Weathers.

55:22.099 --> 55:23.764
I'm a reporter
for Channel 7 in New York.

55:23.891 --> 55:25.172
Mm-hmm.

55:25.300 --> 55:26.868
We're doing a story
on Karl Gibbs.
I figured.

55:26.996 --> 55:30.420
The state police,
they were here all night
going through his stuff.

55:30.932 --> 55:32.116
Can we see his room?

55:32.659 --> 55:33.844
Well...

55:35.156 --> 55:37.044
[groans]

55:37.172 --> 55:39.732
Yeah, I guess so. Come on,
it's right down this way.

55:40.788 --> 55:42.804
So what can you
tell us about Karl?

55:42.932 --> 55:44.532
He was
a pretty violent guy.

55:45.556 --> 55:48.564
Killed three women
about 20 years ago.

55:51.220 --> 55:52.852
Can you think of any reason
that he would

55:52.980 --> 55:55.060
go after Sidney Prescott
and her family?

55:56.052 --> 55:57.972
[Marco] No, not that I know of.

55:59.092 --> 56:00.692
I'm glad you're okay, though.

56:01.172 --> 56:02.708
Thanks.

56:05.748 --> 56:08.596
Did you ever hear him talk
about the Ghostface killings?

56:08.724 --> 56:11.508
Or the <i>Stab</i> movies,
or anything like that?

56:11.636 --> 56:12.692
Not that I remember.

56:12.820 --> 56:14.164
What about, um...

56:14.772 --> 56:15.668
him?

56:15.796 --> 56:17.908
Yeah, that's John.

56:18.739 --> 56:19.828
John?

56:19.955 --> 56:21.267
Yeah, as in John Doe.

56:21.396 --> 56:22.964
He didn't know his real name.

56:23.092 --> 56:24.564
He had amnesia from
the blow to the head

56:24.692 --> 56:26.452
that gave him all those scars.

56:26.580 --> 56:28.020
When did he arrive here?

56:28.148 --> 56:29.460
Well, it was before my time.

56:29.588 --> 56:33.876
I've been here 16 years.
So late '90s, maybe?

56:34.772 --> 56:37.172
His room was right down there.
You want to see it?

56:37.300 --> 56:38.516
Yes.

56:38.644 --> 56:40.404
You know, h-he was a drifter.

56:40.532 --> 56:43.572
Sleeping on the streets
of California or somewhere.

56:44.563 --> 56:46.772
And then one day he snapped.

56:47.412 --> 56:49.556
Attacked a high school girl.

56:49.684 --> 56:53.652
He was declared incompetent to
stand trial and ended up here.

56:54.484 --> 56:57.076
And where is he now?
He was released.

56:58.644 --> 57:00.372
Two weeks ago.

57:00.500 --> 57:02.899
Any idea where he went
after he was released?

57:03.796 --> 57:04.692
No, I'm sorry.

57:04.819 --> 57:05.844
But for that information

57:05.972 --> 57:07.892
you're gonna need
a court order.

57:08.020 --> 57:10.356
And I assume that John Doe
and Karl Gibbs

57:10.483 --> 57:11.795
spent a lot of time together?

57:11.924 --> 57:14.132
Oh, yeah.
No, they were good friends.

57:14.261 --> 57:15.283
Yeah.

57:15.412 --> 57:16.756
[Marco] Very close.

57:17.428 --> 57:18.836
[leaf blower blowing]

57:18.964 --> 57:20.148
Hmm.

57:31.476 --> 57:32.659
Hmm.

57:35.349 --> 57:36.468
[Mindy] Neighbor boy's sus.

57:36.596 --> 57:38.740
He's out there
staring at the house.

57:38.868 --> 57:40.117
Not subtle at all.

57:40.692 --> 57:43.029
I've gone back three days.

57:43.156 --> 57:44.435
If the killer was hiding
in the attic,

57:44.564 --> 57:46.196
he had to go into
the house at some point.

57:46.324 --> 57:48.340
Could the footage be hacked?

57:48.468 --> 57:50.324
Clearly the killer
is tech savvy.

57:50.452 --> 57:51.604
[Chad] I don't know.
[clears throat]

57:51.732 --> 57:53.779
Uh, did you two find
the towels?

57:53.908 --> 57:54.868
You got everything you need?

57:54.995 --> 57:56.756
Yeah, the water
pressure was...

57:56.884 --> 57:58.676
top-notch, so, thank you.

57:58.804 --> 58:00.403
Yeah. Yeah, of course.

58:01.172 --> 58:02.580
So, um...

58:03.379 --> 58:04.595
Why are you here?

58:05.620 --> 58:08.435
I'm sorry, I mean,
um... [scoffs]

58:09.747 --> 58:11.412
After everything
you've been through,

58:12.116 --> 58:13.012
aren't you scared?

58:13.140 --> 58:15.540
[chuckles] Scared. Necessity.

58:15.669 --> 58:18.804
My career trajectory
is to succeed
and exceed Gale Weathers.

58:18.932 --> 58:21.875
And as Woodsboro legacy,
it is our duty.

58:22.932 --> 58:25.140
Our uncle Randy was really
good friends with your mom.

58:25.269 --> 58:28.020
[Mindy] And I want to uncover
the killer this time.

58:28.149 --> 58:29.299
She has been wrong a lot.

58:29.428 --> 58:30.644
That is not supportive.

58:30.772 --> 58:33.877
Un-Uncover a killer?
How do you uncover a killer?

58:34.003 --> 58:38.132
Assemble the suspects
and then Agatha Christie them
until they break.

58:38.260 --> 58:39.828
So-- How do you
know who they are?

58:39.956 --> 58:42.612
If history is any indication,
it's likely
one of your friends.

58:42.739 --> 58:43.828
Probably your boyfriend.

58:43.955 --> 58:45.492
[Chad] Boyfriend's too obvious.

58:45.619 --> 58:47.092
Unless it's by design.

58:47.220 --> 58:48.180
It's not my boyfriend.

58:48.309 --> 58:49.652
[chuckles] That's cute.

58:49.780 --> 58:51.476
We need to gather all the
suspects together in one room.

58:51.604 --> 58:55.348
Well, there's
a curfew at sundown.
The whole town's closing up.

58:57.364 --> 58:58.740
Actually, there might be a way.

58:58.869 --> 59:01.556
I just would have to figure
out how to get around my dad.

59:01.685 --> 59:03.412
[Chad] Is that possible?

59:03.540 --> 59:05.140
He is the police chief.

59:05.268 --> 59:08.148
But if we can find out
who's doing this,
then he can go get them.

59:08.276 --> 59:09.940
If we can help, we should.

59:11.924 --> 59:13.363
I'm sick of being useless.

59:15.572 --> 59:16.981
That was Deputy Cooke.

59:17.109 --> 59:19.508
They're set up to trace his
phone if he calls me again.

59:19.636 --> 59:21.492
So we just have to
wait for him to call?

59:21.620 --> 59:24.436
Oh, come on,
there's got to be some way to
bait him into calling you.

59:25.781 --> 59:29.332
What if I gave you what you've
been asking me for since 1996?

59:30.581 --> 59:31.764
An interview.

59:33.875 --> 59:35.764
Get the fuck out of here.

59:35.892 --> 59:37.780
Look, I just need an ETA
on that court order.

59:37.908 --> 59:39.828
[Cooke] <i>You got it, Chief.</i>
<i>I'll take care of it.</i>

59:39.956 --> 59:42.612
Good. Okay. Call me
the second Sid's phone rings.

59:44.148 --> 59:45.043
Tatum!

59:45.172 --> 59:46.484
[clattering]

59:53.493 --> 59:54.836
[clattering]

01:01:26.899 --> 01:01:28.084
[electrical buzzing]

01:01:39.157 --> 01:01:40.724
[screams]

01:01:45.588 --> 01:01:47.092
[screaming]

01:01:54.612 --> 01:01:56.052
["Red Right Hand" playing]

01:01:56.181 --> 01:02:00.596
♪ <i>...to the edge of town</i>
<i>Go across the tracks</i> ♪

01:02:01.748 --> 01:02:06.132
♪ <i>Where the viaduct looms</i>
<i>Like a bird of doom</i> ♪

01:02:06.259 --> 01:02:07.348
♪ <i>As it shifts...</i> ♪

01:02:07.475 --> 01:02:09.877
[owner] Okay.
Get home safe. Bye, guys.

01:02:10.003 --> 01:02:14.100
♪ <i>Where secrets lie</i>
<i>In the border fires</i> ♪

01:02:14.228 --> 01:02:16.020
♪ <i>In the humming wires</i> ♪

01:02:16.148 --> 01:02:18.995
♪ <i>Hey man, you know</i>
<i>You're never coming back</i> ♪

01:02:19.124 --> 01:02:21.044
♪ <i>Past this square</i>
<i>Past the bridge</i> ♪

01:02:21.172 --> 01:02:23.924
♪ <i>Past the mills</i>
<i>Past the stacks</i> ♪

01:02:25.876 --> 01:02:29.716
♪ <i>On a gathering storm</i>
<i>Comes a tall, handsome man</i> ♪

01:02:29.845 --> 01:02:34.612
♪ <i>In a dusty black coat</i>
<i>With a red right hand</i> ♪

01:02:36.789 --> 01:02:37.843
Hey.
Hey, Chlo.

01:02:37.972 --> 01:02:39.188
Ben and Lucas
are already here.

01:02:39.316 --> 01:02:42.325
All right. Uh,
this is Chad and Mindy.

01:02:42.453 --> 01:02:44.245
Hi. I'm Chloe. Come on in.

01:02:46.069 --> 01:02:47.956
[Chad] So your parents
own this place.

01:02:48.085 --> 01:02:50.644
[Chloe] Yes, but they
don't know we're here,
so we got to lay low.

01:02:51.444 --> 01:02:52.628
How you doing?

01:02:53.492 --> 01:02:55.284
[Chloe] What are
we drinking, kids?

01:02:56.212 --> 01:02:57.428
Here is...

01:02:57.557 --> 01:02:59.797
[singsongy] ...the
pepperoni and mushroom pizza.

01:02:59.923 --> 01:03:01.268
[Tatum] Thanks, Chlo.
[Chad] Thank you.

01:03:01.397 --> 01:03:03.060
So what is the deal
with you two?

01:03:03.188 --> 01:03:05.908
[Tatum] Um, they want to help
us find out who's doing this.

01:03:06.035 --> 01:03:08.915
What, they think
it's one of us?

01:03:09.044 --> 01:03:10.452
[Mindy chuckles]

01:03:12.085 --> 01:03:14.388
Yeah. But I don't.

01:03:15.604 --> 01:03:17.428
So this dead dude from thirty
years ago, he is not so dead?

01:03:17.555 --> 01:03:19.475
How could Stu Macher
really be alive?

01:03:20.052 --> 01:03:21.492
Where's he been? Under a rock?

01:03:21.621 --> 01:03:23.444
Nobody recognized him
for three decades?

01:03:23.572 --> 01:03:26.260
That's a ridiculous retcon
for any franchise.

01:03:26.389 --> 01:03:29.140
See, this time it is
all about nostalgia.

01:03:29.269 --> 01:03:31.348
Hey, Min! We talked about
the rules thing,

01:03:31.477 --> 01:03:33.333
we said we weren't gonna
do that anymore. We're better
than that. So just...

01:03:33.461 --> 01:03:37.141
Okay. Whoever it is
wants to bring Sidney
out of retirement.

01:03:37.269 --> 01:03:40.085
She's a scream queen.
Scream queens are not allowed
to have happy endings.

01:03:40.212 --> 01:03:43.828
There's a reason they
keep putting Jamie Lee
in new <i>Halloween</i> movies.

01:03:43.957 --> 01:03:45.909
We all want to read
<i>Wuthering Heights</i>
again for the first time.

01:03:46.036 --> 01:03:47.445
But this is real life.

01:03:47.572 --> 01:03:49.235
Yes, exactly.

01:03:49.365 --> 01:03:51.669
This person isn't a fan of
<i>Stab</i> movies,

01:03:51.796 --> 01:03:54.100
they're a fan of
Sidney Prescott.

01:03:54.229 --> 01:03:55.860
Not the Sidney of today,
though.

01:03:55.988 --> 01:03:58.293
The Sidney
of thirty years ago.

01:03:58.421 --> 01:04:01.237
The Sidney that was killing
Ghostfaces, like, once a year.

01:04:01.363 --> 01:04:03.668
And the reason they're using
Stu Macher to fuck with her

01:04:03.797 --> 01:04:06.259
is because he was
there at the start.

01:04:06.388 --> 01:04:10.003
The night Sidney the
Avenging Angel was born.

01:04:10.132 --> 01:04:11.701
[whistles]

01:04:11.829 --> 01:04:14.004
Or it really is Stu.
I mean, Billy Loomis
had a secret love child,

01:04:14.132 --> 01:04:15.859
so who the fuck knows anymore?

01:04:15.988 --> 01:04:17.428
Where'd you get these calls?
Uh...

01:04:17.557 --> 01:04:20.852
My mom's cloud. Can you
tell if they're fake or not?

01:04:20.980 --> 01:04:22.261
If it's a fake,
it's a good one.
Hmm.

01:04:22.389 --> 01:04:24.021
The shadows are consistent.

01:04:24.148 --> 01:04:27.412
The eyes, hands, they all have
zero artifacts or pixilation.
I mean...

01:04:27.540 --> 01:04:28.757
These might have
been live calls.

01:04:28.885 --> 01:04:31.605
All right, well,
if it is Stu Macher

01:04:31.732 --> 01:04:33.717
then we know
he has an accomplice.

01:04:33.845 --> 01:04:36.341
He can't be in two
places at once, so...

01:04:37.781 --> 01:04:39.124
who is it?

01:04:39.253 --> 01:04:41.012
Why would any of us want to
terrorize Tatum and her mom?

01:04:41.141 --> 01:04:44.405
Why indeed. Let's talk motive.

01:04:44.532 --> 01:04:45.973
Pardon. Thank you.

01:04:46.101 --> 01:04:48.245
Okay, Ben.
Mmm.

01:04:48.372 --> 01:04:50.901
Does Sidney truly approve
of you as Tatum's boyfriend?

01:04:51.028 --> 01:04:54.515
Moms never like the boyfriend.
That's Mommy 101, there.

01:04:54.645 --> 01:04:57.525
And you're an interesting
mix of brawn and brains.

01:04:57.652 --> 01:05:00.084
Nah. I like to work out
my body and my mind, yeah.

01:05:00.212 --> 01:05:01.908
See, that's incredibly
bizarre to say out loud.

01:05:02.036 --> 01:05:03.669
[Mindy] Chloe.

01:05:03.796 --> 01:05:05.525
Hey.
[Mindy]
Fun-loving. Everyone likes.

01:05:05.652 --> 01:05:08.021
Excellent hair.
Seemingly has no motive.

01:05:08.149 --> 01:05:09.333
That's me.

01:05:09.461 --> 01:05:10.612
I'm not buying it.
[Chloe] Good.

01:05:10.740 --> 01:05:12.213
I don't like a girl
that everyone likes.

01:05:12.341 --> 01:05:13.620
It's boring.

01:05:13.749 --> 01:05:15.925
Oh. See? That's motive.

01:05:16.053 --> 01:05:18.677
Right? Boredom? Now we're
in Stu Macher territory.

01:05:18.805 --> 01:05:20.725
[Mindy]
And you, weird boy.
Okay.

01:05:20.853 --> 01:05:24.341
You've displayed
an unsettling obsession with
all things Sidney Prescott.

01:05:24.469 --> 01:05:26.261
She's a pinnacle in
the true-crime lexicon.

01:05:26.389 --> 01:05:27.859
I'm not obsessed.
I'm just...

01:05:27.988 --> 01:05:30.804
I'm, uh, fascinated.

01:05:30.932 --> 01:05:33.365
Splitting hairs,
young man.

01:05:33.492 --> 01:05:34.740
Okay, my money's on boyfriend.

01:05:34.869 --> 01:05:36.213
Yeah, my bet's
on creepy kid.

01:05:36.341 --> 01:05:37.556
Okay,
I'm pretty fucking sick of

01:05:37.684 --> 01:05:39.252
all this "creepy" shit,
all right?

01:05:39.379 --> 01:05:40.789
I'm not creepy.

01:05:40.917 --> 01:05:42.965
Creepy is kind of hot.

01:05:43.092 --> 01:05:44.276
[gasps]

01:05:45.108 --> 01:05:46.645
Oh.
Hey.

01:05:46.773 --> 01:05:47.956
Hey.

01:05:49.044 --> 01:05:50.485
Can I have another beer?

01:05:50.613 --> 01:05:52.052
You can have
whatever you want.

01:05:55.509 --> 01:05:58.101
[Robbie]
And per our discussion,
this is my exclusive.

01:05:58.228 --> 01:06:00.021
That was the deal.
[Gale] Yeah, yeah. Got it.

01:06:00.148 --> 01:06:02.261
[Robbie] Okay.
[Gale exhales] There you go.

01:06:02.388 --> 01:06:03.604
Oh, okay.

01:06:03.733 --> 01:06:05.268
Oh. There.

01:06:05.396 --> 01:06:06.452
[Robbie sighs]

01:06:06.581 --> 01:06:08.212
All right,
I have three cameras on you.

01:06:08.340 --> 01:06:10.003
We'll be operating from
the control room.

01:06:10.132 --> 01:06:12.789
We need your phone,
so when he calls...

01:06:13.397 --> 01:06:15.508
Thank you.
All right, ladies,

01:06:15.637 --> 01:06:19.221
we'll be ready to break into
every affiliate in the state
on your go.

01:06:19.860 --> 01:06:21.973
Jesus, this is
fucking awesome!

01:06:22.579 --> 01:06:23.668
[Gale] Okay.

01:06:23.796 --> 01:06:25.845
Let's just hope that
Stu is watching.

01:06:26.323 --> 01:06:27.316
Ready?

01:06:27.444 --> 01:06:29.460
You gonna play nice?
Of course not.

01:06:29.589 --> 01:06:32.629
I've been waiting for this
interview for thirty years.

01:06:32.757 --> 01:06:34.196
And three, two...

01:06:34.325 --> 01:06:36.116
[theme music playing]

01:06:36.245 --> 01:06:40.629
Hi, I'm Gale Weathers
here for an exclusive interview
with Sidney Prescott.

01:06:40.756 --> 01:06:42.996
[phone chimes]
[Lucas, Chloe chattering]

01:06:44.628 --> 01:06:45.941
What the hell?

01:06:46.069 --> 01:06:48.917
My mom's going live on TV.
Channel 7.

01:06:49.045 --> 01:06:50.037
Oh.

01:06:52.725 --> 01:06:55.029
<i>Welcome, Sidney. Hi.</i>
<i>Hi, Gale.</i>

01:06:55.156 --> 01:06:59.220
<i>So everyone knows you as</i>
<i>the survivor of</i>
<i>many brutal attacks.</i>

01:06:59.349 --> 01:07:03.573
<i>And I understand that</i>
<i>you and your family</i>
<i>are once again a target.</i>

01:07:03.701 --> 01:07:05.621
Can you explain
what's happening?

01:07:05.748 --> 01:07:07.668
My family and I
have been attacked twice now

01:07:07.796 --> 01:07:10.325
by someone claiming to be
Stu Macher.

01:07:10.452 --> 01:07:12.468
But Stu was
killed in Woodsboro

01:07:12.596 --> 01:07:15.508
the night that he
and Billy Loomis attacked you.

01:07:15.636 --> 01:07:19.156
Yes, but now
I'm not so sure.

01:07:19.284 --> 01:07:21.204
Is that why you're doing
this interview?

01:07:21.333 --> 01:07:24.019
I want to talk to him.
What would you
like to say?

01:07:24.148 --> 01:07:26.581
I want to know
what he wants.

01:07:26.709 --> 01:07:29.365
Why he's doing this
after all of these years.

01:07:29.493 --> 01:07:31.093
I want him to know that

01:07:31.989 --> 01:07:33.588
this doesn't need to continue.

01:07:33.716 --> 01:07:35.349
Zoom in.
Tighter, tighter.

01:07:35.476 --> 01:07:37.749
Whatever you need, let's talk.

01:07:37.877 --> 01:07:38.869
Hmm.

01:07:39.988 --> 01:07:42.101
Maybe he's too much of
a little bitch.

01:07:42.901 --> 01:07:45.652
He always was the sidekick,
never the lead.

01:07:47.765 --> 01:07:49.205
Is that what it is?

01:07:49.333 --> 01:07:52.533
You want to be the lead?
Well, here you go.

01:07:52.661 --> 01:07:54.453
<i>Call me. You have a platform.</i>

01:07:54.581 --> 01:07:55.893
Oh, shit.

01:07:59.957 --> 01:08:03.379
Maybe he hasn't tuned in yet.
Let's keep talking.

01:08:04.339 --> 01:08:06.613
You and I have known
each other a long time.

01:08:07.349 --> 01:08:09.043
A very long time, yes.
[clears throat]

01:08:09.172 --> 01:08:11.092
How would you describe
our relationship?

01:08:12.149 --> 01:08:14.036
Complicated but enduring.

01:08:15.156 --> 01:08:17.013
You wrote a book,
<i>Out of Darkness,</i>

01:08:17.141 --> 01:08:18.933
<i>about healing your trauma.</i>

01:08:19.061 --> 01:08:21.492
<i>And yet you have</i>
<i>completely disappeared</i>

01:08:21.619 --> 01:08:24.148
<i>from the public eye</i>
<i>for years now. Why?</i>

01:08:24.277 --> 01:08:28.053
<i>It just seemed</i>
<i>the more I talked about it,</i>
<i>the more darkness came.</i>

01:08:28.181 --> 01:08:29.141
Mmm.

01:08:29.268 --> 01:08:30.421
You have three children.

01:08:30.549 --> 01:08:32.917
Tatum being your oldest.
She's seventeen?

01:08:33.043 --> 01:08:34.612
I'd rather not talk about
my children.

01:08:34.741 --> 01:08:38.293
Tatum is the same age
that you were
when this whole thing started.

01:08:38.421 --> 01:08:40.437
That must have
a huge significance for you.

01:08:40.565 --> 01:08:42.772
Like I said, I don't want to
talk about my kids.

01:08:42.901 --> 01:08:44.916
[Gale]
<i>And you named your kid Tatum</i>

01:08:45.045 --> 01:08:48.661
<i>after the young girl who was</i>
<i>brutally murdered</i>
<i>all those years ago.</i>

01:08:48.789 --> 01:08:52.501
I named her after a childhood
friend whom I loved dearly.

01:08:54.196 --> 01:08:56.565
She was the last friend
I ever trusted.

01:08:58.356 --> 01:08:59.349
Mmm.

01:09:00.019 --> 01:09:01.109
Sidney, do you ever
worry about

01:09:01.236 --> 01:09:03.381
passing your trauma on
to your children?

01:09:03.508 --> 01:09:04.723
Or, even worse yet,

01:09:04.852 --> 01:09:06.643
that they would be
the target of future killings?

01:09:06.772 --> 01:09:07.925
Oh, shit.

01:09:08.053 --> 01:09:09.973
[Gale] Sidney?
Okay, Gale, stop.

01:09:12.245 --> 01:09:14.741
Where's she going?
Okay, we'll be right back.

01:09:14.869 --> 01:09:17.077
Or maybe not. Cut.

01:09:17.203 --> 01:09:18.228
All right.

01:09:18.357 --> 01:09:20.309
Um... Go to the outro
and stand by.

01:09:20.436 --> 01:09:22.261
[theme music playing]
Wh--

01:09:24.725 --> 01:09:25.973
That was unfair.

01:09:26.389 --> 01:09:28.053
And dangerous!

01:09:28.181 --> 01:09:30.549
But you disappeared, Sid.
People want to know.

01:09:30.676 --> 01:09:32.181
I want to know!

01:09:32.981 --> 01:09:34.933
I'm sorry.
Are you?

01:09:35.061 --> 01:09:38.261
What if I had asked you
about Dewey on live TV?

01:09:38.388 --> 01:09:39.283
What would you say?

01:09:39.413 --> 01:09:41.685
Well, I'd say I'm fine.

01:09:42.933 --> 01:09:46.003
Because that's what I
tell myself 500 times a day

01:09:46.133 --> 01:09:48.149
just to get through the day.

01:10:07.156 --> 01:10:09.941
<i>This has been a Robbie Rivers</i>
<i>exclusive with Gale Weathers</i>

01:10:10.068 --> 01:10:12.821
<i>and Pine Grove's very</i>
<i>own Sidney Prescott Evans.</i>

01:10:12.980 --> 01:10:14.357
<i>We will be monitoring--</i>

01:10:14.485 --> 01:10:16.181
That was intense.

01:10:17.621 --> 01:10:18.805
Yeah.

01:10:19.445 --> 01:10:20.628
Are you okay?

01:10:23.476 --> 01:10:25.012
I'm sorry this is happening.

01:10:25.685 --> 01:10:28.085
And this--
This was a dumb idea.

01:10:28.212 --> 01:10:29.429
How far is the TV station?

01:10:29.556 --> 01:10:31.285
I just really want to be with
my mom right now.

01:10:31.413 --> 01:10:33.173
We're super close.
I mean, I'll take you.

01:10:33.652 --> 01:10:34.901
Okay.

01:10:35.029 --> 01:10:36.245
[phone ringing]

01:10:37.492 --> 01:10:39.093
[breathes deeply]

01:10:41.525 --> 01:10:42.643
We're not on air.

01:10:42.773 --> 01:10:44.629
And this needs to be
on air.
Hello?

01:10:44.757 --> 01:10:47.285
<i>Aw, Sid, do you need a hug?</i>

01:10:47.412 --> 01:10:48.789
[mocking crying]

01:10:48.917 --> 01:10:50.389
We've been waiting for you.

01:10:50.517 --> 01:10:51.573
<i>Why? So I can</i>
<i>stay on the phone</i>

01:10:51.701 --> 01:10:53.013
<i>long enough for you to</i>
<i>trace the call?</i>

01:10:53.141 --> 01:10:55.797
Yes, dumbass! Or you could
just tell us where you are.

01:10:55.925 --> 01:10:58.677
<i>Great. I am at Parker's Tavern</i>

01:10:58.805 --> 01:11:00.469
<i>with your daughter.</i>

01:11:01.205 --> 01:11:02.709
My daughter's not at Parker's.

01:11:02.837 --> 01:11:04.372
<i>Well, she's definitely not</i>
<i>at home.</i>

01:11:04.501 --> 01:11:06.165
[chuckles] <i>She broke curfew.</i>

01:11:06.292 --> 01:11:08.053
<i>She's a bad bitch.</i>

01:11:08.597 --> 01:11:10.037
<i>I'm gonna punish her.</i>

01:11:10.997 --> 01:11:12.181
Fuck.

01:11:12.309 --> 01:11:13.685
Is that it?
Is he gonna call back?

01:11:13.813 --> 01:11:15.252
Because you said
this was my story.

01:11:15.380 --> 01:11:16.437
Where's the story, Gale?
Stop!

01:11:16.565 --> 01:11:18.293
You need to
call the police right now,

01:11:18.421 --> 01:11:20.533
tell them to go to
Parker's Tavern.

01:11:21.173 --> 01:11:22.356
Sidney!

01:11:23.637 --> 01:11:25.013
Sidney!

01:11:25.781 --> 01:11:26.933
Oh, fuck.

01:11:27.061 --> 01:11:28.949
Mark, Tatum went
to Chloe's restaurant.

01:11:29.076 --> 01:11:30.165
She's in trouble.

01:11:30.292 --> 01:11:31.509
Where are you?

01:11:31.637 --> 01:11:32.532
Damn it!

01:11:32.660 --> 01:11:34.228
[breathing heavily]

01:11:36.341 --> 01:11:37.525
Oh, fuck.

01:11:39.061 --> 01:11:40.917
[intense music playing]

01:11:48.020 --> 01:11:49.205
Thanks.

01:11:58.645 --> 01:11:59.957
What is this?
Hmm?

01:12:00.085 --> 01:12:01.364
Oh, uh...

01:12:01.493 --> 01:12:04.373
[Tatum]
Did you create this?
[Ben] What? No.

01:12:04.501 --> 01:12:06.645
I created that one just
to see if it was possible.

01:12:06.772 --> 01:12:09.140
<i>I can't wait to fucking</i>
<i>kill you, Sidney Prescott,</i>

01:12:09.269 --> 01:12:10.677
<i>and your daughter.</i>

01:12:10.805 --> 01:12:14.165
<i>And I'm gonna love</i>
<i>every second of it, you bitch!</i>

01:12:14.293 --> 01:12:15.029
Tate.

01:12:15.156 --> 01:12:17.525
It was you.
No, it wasn't.

01:12:17.653 --> 01:12:19.221
[groans]
[gasps]

01:12:19.348 --> 01:12:20.853
Tate.
[grunts]

01:12:33.365 --> 01:12:35.541
You know, not exactly
a roaring success, Min.

01:12:35.668 --> 01:12:37.492
We still have no idea
who the killer is.

01:12:37.621 --> 01:12:39.285
Creepy kid still has my vote.

01:12:39.412 --> 01:12:40.468
I'm way too obvious.

01:12:40.597 --> 01:12:42.805
So obvious
it's not obvious.

01:12:42.933 --> 01:12:44.502
What is that smell?

01:12:45.077 --> 01:12:48.052
Oh, shit! Pizza's in the oven.

01:12:50.420 --> 01:12:51.925
Bathroom break.

01:12:54.997 --> 01:12:58.325
We should not have left Tatum
alone with Gen-Z Billy Loomis.

01:12:58.453 --> 01:12:59.924
Okay? I'm not feeling good
about that.

01:13:00.053 --> 01:13:02.421
Do you find it weird
that two very real suspects

01:13:02.548 --> 01:13:03.669
just conveniently disappeared?

01:13:04.565 --> 01:13:05.909
I really don't want
to get stabbed tonight.

01:13:06.036 --> 01:13:07.861
Let's go find Tatum.

01:13:09.301 --> 01:13:10.741
Okay.

01:13:14.293 --> 01:13:16.277
It's locked.
We are locked in.

01:13:16.405 --> 01:13:19.029
[sighs] There must be
another way out of here.

01:13:19.157 --> 01:13:20.405
Let's try
the dining room.

01:13:21.781 --> 01:13:23.924
[lights buzzing]

01:13:34.869 --> 01:13:36.981
Oven's a piece of shit.

01:13:38.357 --> 01:13:40.693
[sighs]
[clattering]

01:13:56.469 --> 01:13:58.005
[gasps]

01:14:05.173 --> 01:14:06.325
Fuck.

01:14:08.373 --> 01:14:09.748
[breathing heavily]

01:14:13.686 --> 01:14:16.149
Where's the fucking door?

01:14:20.789 --> 01:14:22.326
Hey. The kitchen.

01:14:22.453 --> 01:14:24.404
There has to be a back door.

01:14:24.533 --> 01:14:25.716
[clattering]

01:14:27.988 --> 01:14:29.333
That's not good.

01:14:37.653 --> 01:14:39.317
[gasps, groans]

01:14:43.157 --> 01:14:44.853
[shouts, grunts]

01:14:52.086 --> 01:14:54.260
[screams, grunts]

01:14:59.509 --> 01:15:01.173
[grunts]
[groans]

01:15:04.245 --> 01:15:05.237
Aw, shit.

01:15:06.005 --> 01:15:07.348
[Mindy] Hey, cupcake!

01:15:09.013 --> 01:15:10.741
[groans]

01:15:17.781 --> 01:15:19.285
Hey, hey, hey.
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

01:15:19.413 --> 01:15:21.109
The killer is in there.
Hey, hey. I got this.

01:15:21.237 --> 01:15:23.221
Don't go in there.
It's okay, I got this.

01:15:23.349 --> 01:15:25.588
I got this, I got this!

01:15:26.900 --> 01:15:28.116
Lucas!

01:15:40.244 --> 01:15:42.164
[Lucas coughs]
[Chloe] Oh, my God.

01:15:42.902 --> 01:15:44.245
Oh, God.

01:15:48.853 --> 01:15:50.997
[keys jingling]

01:15:51.574 --> 01:15:52.372
[clattering]

01:15:52.502 --> 01:15:53.749
[gasps]

01:15:59.540 --> 01:16:00.789
Fuck.

01:16:07.317 --> 01:16:09.013
[footsteps thudding]

01:16:14.997 --> 01:16:16.789
[footsteps stop]

01:16:35.189 --> 01:16:37.269
[breathing shakily]

01:16:37.397 --> 01:16:38.804
[Lucas grunting]

01:16:38.933 --> 01:16:40.981
[door opens]

01:16:50.038 --> 01:16:51.253
[Chloe] Lucas.

01:16:52.118 --> 01:16:53.333
[screams]

01:17:06.837 --> 01:17:08.693
[choking, gurgling]

01:17:18.421 --> 01:17:21.013
[gasps, groans]

01:17:31.509 --> 01:17:32.821
No.

01:17:40.149 --> 01:17:42.966
No. Help. No.

01:17:43.093 --> 01:17:46.485
No, no, no. No! [coughs]

01:18:07.989 --> 01:18:09.461
[groans]

01:18:18.389 --> 01:18:20.564
[gurgling]

01:18:31.220 --> 01:18:32.789
[crickets chirping]

01:18:33.686 --> 01:18:35.477
[dog barking]
[Tatum breathing heavily]

01:18:48.373 --> 01:18:49.269
No!

01:18:49.397 --> 01:18:51.701
[ominous music plays]

01:18:53.942 --> 01:18:55.573
Open up, please! Please!

01:18:55.702 --> 01:18:57.205
Come on! [grunts]

01:19:02.997 --> 01:19:04.917
[suspenseful music plays]

01:19:05.877 --> 01:19:07.573
[footsteps approaching]

01:19:08.564 --> 01:19:09.973
[shouts, grunts]

01:19:13.910 --> 01:19:16.182
Help! Please,
somebody help me!

01:19:16.309 --> 01:19:19.349
He's trying to kill me!
Please!

01:19:19.476 --> 01:19:22.678
Someone help me! [shrieks]

01:19:25.813 --> 01:19:27.413
[screams]

01:19:32.278 --> 01:19:33.524
[grunting]

01:19:40.405 --> 01:19:42.229
[music stops]

01:19:52.566 --> 01:19:54.709
[breathing heavily]

01:19:55.861 --> 01:19:57.493
[ominous music plays]

01:20:13.877 --> 01:20:15.669
[screams]
I found you.

01:20:15.797 --> 01:20:17.333
Did you see him? The killer?

01:20:17.462 --> 01:20:20.533
No, I didn't see anyone.
You hit me.
Got me real good, too.

01:20:20.660 --> 01:20:22.038
We have to get out of here.

01:20:22.166 --> 01:20:23.413
Tate, listen.

01:20:23.540 --> 01:20:24.629
It's not me, Tate.

01:20:24.756 --> 01:20:27.798
I know. I know, I'm sorry.

01:20:28.533 --> 01:20:30.806
I would never hurt you, okay?

01:20:37.462 --> 01:20:38.582
No!

01:20:38.709 --> 01:20:40.116
[alarm blaring]

01:20:49.910 --> 01:20:51.284
Help!

01:21:06.709 --> 01:21:08.150
[door buzzes]

01:21:17.525 --> 01:21:19.606
[Sidney breathing heavily]

01:21:33.974 --> 01:21:35.413
[rattling]

01:21:53.270 --> 01:21:54.805
[phone rings]

01:22:11.798 --> 01:22:15.157
[tense music playing]

01:22:19.318 --> 01:22:20.693
Oh, God.

01:22:21.238 --> 01:22:22.806
[breathes heavily]

01:22:38.678 --> 01:22:40.054
[knocking on door]

01:22:45.302 --> 01:22:46.741
[keypad beeping]

01:22:48.053 --> 01:22:49.717
[door buzzes]

01:22:56.213 --> 01:22:58.261
[grunting]

01:23:14.166 --> 01:23:15.349
[Sidney] Oh, God.

01:23:18.869 --> 01:23:20.213
[screams]

01:23:22.229 --> 01:23:24.726
[Sidney on phone] <i>Tatum.</i>
Mom!

01:23:24.853 --> 01:23:26.197
I'm coming, okay?

01:23:26.326 --> 01:23:28.054
[Tatum, distorted dialogue]
<i>He's at the door!</i>

01:23:28.182 --> 01:23:31.957
Oh, shit. Oh, shit.
[Tatum crying, distorted]

01:23:32.469 --> 01:23:34.358
Oh, fuck you, phone.

01:23:34.484 --> 01:23:36.342
[Tatum] <i>I can't hear you!</i>
<i>I can't hear you!</i>

01:23:36.469 --> 01:23:38.966
Okay. Okay.

01:23:39.830 --> 01:23:40.918
Tatum, listen to me.

01:23:41.046 --> 01:23:42.229
I'm not gonna make it in time.

01:23:42.357 --> 01:23:44.180
<i>But I'm gonna stay with you.</i>

01:23:44.310 --> 01:23:46.678
<i>You need to get the gun.</i>
<i>It's in the safe.</i>

01:23:46.806 --> 01:23:48.406
[pounding on door]

01:23:48.533 --> 01:23:49.686
Okay.

01:23:49.813 --> 01:23:51.413
The code is your birthday.

01:24:00.854 --> 01:24:02.742
[stammering] I don't know
how to use this.

01:24:02.870 --> 01:24:05.590
I'm gonna talk you through it.
You have your earbuds?

01:24:05.718 --> 01:24:08.053
Well, put them in, okay?
You're gonna need both hands.

01:24:08.180 --> 01:24:09.366
[Tatum] <i>Okay.</i>

01:24:11.924 --> 01:24:14.518
[pounding]

01:24:16.820 --> 01:24:18.709
Okay. Okay.
[pounding stops]

01:24:20.469 --> 01:24:21.653
Wait.

01:24:22.710 --> 01:24:24.854
<i>I don't hear him.</i>
<i>I think he left.</i>

01:24:26.453 --> 01:24:28.277
No, he's trying to find
another way in.

01:24:28.405 --> 01:24:30.325
[pounding resumes]
Oh, Mom, hurry!

01:24:30.454 --> 01:24:32.566
Okay, baby, listen to me.

01:24:32.693 --> 01:24:35.478
[stammering] The gun is--
It's loaded,

01:24:35.606 --> 01:24:38.582
so you have to turn
the safety off, all right?

01:24:38.709 --> 01:24:40.342
You see that little switch?

01:24:40.918 --> 01:24:42.901
<i>Flip it up. There's a red dot.</i>

01:24:43.030 --> 01:24:44.246
[gun clicks]
I see it.

01:24:44.374 --> 01:24:47.766
Okay. So all you have to
do now is you point

01:24:47.894 --> 01:24:51.317
<i>and you pull the trigger.</i>
<i>You aim for center mass, okay?</i>

01:24:51.446 --> 01:24:53.494
And when he goes down,
you shoot him in the head.

01:24:55.381 --> 01:24:58.069
[sobbing] I can't.

01:24:58.806 --> 01:25:01.622
I'm not like you. I can't.

01:25:01.749 --> 01:25:02.966
Tatum, you are.

01:25:03.094 --> 01:25:04.693
<i>You are like me.</i>

01:25:04.820 --> 01:25:06.644
I saw your interview.

01:25:07.382 --> 01:25:08.374
Baby, focus.

01:25:08.502 --> 01:25:10.389
<i>We're gonna do this together.</i>

01:25:10.517 --> 01:25:12.469
[sobbing]

01:25:12.598 --> 01:25:14.357
He killed Ben.

01:25:15.380 --> 01:25:17.526
<i>He killed him.</i>

01:25:18.358 --> 01:25:21.334
Right now
you need to survive. Okay?

01:25:21.462 --> 01:25:23.669
That is what's important
right now.

01:25:26.934 --> 01:25:29.142
[shattering]

01:25:29.878 --> 01:25:31.158
[Sidney] <i>Okay.</i>

01:25:31.286 --> 01:25:33.686
You're gonna have to shoot him
through the wall.

01:25:34.166 --> 01:25:35.158
[Tatum] <i>Where?</i>

01:25:36.149 --> 01:25:37.846
[Sidney] <i>Okay, you're gonna</i>
<i>shoot the calendar.</i>

01:25:37.973 --> 01:25:39.830
Fire through the calendar.
No, wait.

01:25:39.958 --> 01:25:41.014
Wait. He's moving.

01:25:41.142 --> 01:25:42.326
Mom?

01:25:42.869 --> 01:25:43.702
To the right of the door.

01:25:43.829 --> 01:25:45.366
Shoot him now! Do it now!

01:25:45.494 --> 01:25:46.550
[screams]

01:25:50.358 --> 01:25:51.318
Oh, you got him.

01:25:51.446 --> 01:25:53.749
[breathing heavily]

01:25:56.182 --> 01:25:57.750
You got him.

01:25:57.877 --> 01:25:59.030
Okay.

01:26:18.870 --> 01:26:20.309
Okay, listen, you're gonna
have to walk around him.

01:26:20.438 --> 01:26:22.741
But before you do that,
you shoot him in the head.

01:26:23.670 --> 01:26:25.973
But he's dead, I got him.

01:26:26.102 --> 01:26:27.830
[Sidney] <i>I know, baby.</i>
<i>You need to make sure.</i>

01:26:27.958 --> 01:26:30.806
You shoot him. You shoot him
in the head right now.

01:26:31.318 --> 01:26:32.693
[Tatum screams]

01:26:33.141 --> 01:26:35.158
Tatum... Tatum!

01:26:37.398 --> 01:26:38.262
Tatum!

01:26:38.390 --> 01:26:39.990
Mom! Mom!

01:26:53.270 --> 01:26:55.414
[grunts]

01:27:16.086 --> 01:27:17.078
[Tatum gasps]

01:27:17.204 --> 01:27:19.733
[menacing music playing]

01:27:24.118 --> 01:27:27.190
[screaming]

01:27:28.918 --> 01:27:30.006
[footsteps approaching]

01:27:30.134 --> 01:27:31.798
Tatum!

01:27:36.534 --> 01:27:38.838
[phone ringing]

01:27:38.966 --> 01:27:42.710
[caller] <i>Hello, Sidney.</i>
<i>Are we having fun yet?</i>

01:27:42.838 --> 01:27:44.053
If you hurt her...

01:27:44.181 --> 01:27:46.550
<i>Relax.</i>
<i>I'm not going to hurt her</i>

01:27:46.678 --> 01:27:48.789
<i>until you're here</i>
<i>to see it.</i>

01:27:48.918 --> 01:27:51.606
Where are you?
<i>Where the heart is...</i>

01:27:51.733 --> 01:27:54.422
<i>until I stab a knife</i>
<i>through it.</i>

01:27:54.549 --> 01:27:56.150
<i>Come alone.</i>

01:28:11.221 --> 01:28:12.629
[breathes shakily]

01:28:46.518 --> 01:28:48.374
[Ghostface]
<i>Welcome home, Sidney.</i>

01:28:48.501 --> 01:28:50.390
<i>We've been waiting for you.</i>

01:28:50.518 --> 01:28:52.086
[Stu, distorted]
<i>Waiting for you.</i>

01:28:52.662 --> 01:28:53.974
<i>Thanks for coming alone.</i>

01:28:54.103 --> 01:28:57.078
<i>It makes it so much easier</i>
<i>that you followed the rules.</i>

01:28:57.206 --> 01:28:58.422
Stop this shit.

01:28:58.550 --> 01:29:00.406
If you're Stu, show yourself!
[Stu chuckles]

01:29:01.718 --> 01:29:03.413
<i>Where am I?</i>

01:29:06.741 --> 01:29:08.278
<i>Can you find me?</i>

01:29:09.621 --> 01:29:11.093
<i>It's not really me.</i>

01:29:11.990 --> 01:29:13.942
<i>You want to know</i>
<i>who I really am?</i>

01:29:17.301 --> 01:29:18.742
<i>Remember me?</i>

01:29:19.638 --> 01:29:22.070
<i>I'll never forgive you for</i>
<i>what you did to my son.</i>

01:29:22.198 --> 01:29:24.598
And you know what?
I would do it again and again.

01:29:24.726 --> 01:29:26.901
<i>Your mother destroyed my life.</i>

01:29:27.030 --> 01:29:28.502
<i>But let's face it.</i>

01:29:28.630 --> 01:29:30.645
<i>She destroyed you, too.</i>

01:29:32.150 --> 01:29:34.998
<i>In the same way that you've</i>
<i>destroyed your own daughter.</i>

01:29:35.126 --> 01:29:36.886
Fuck whoever you are!

01:29:37.013 --> 01:29:38.230
[chuckling]

01:29:38.358 --> 01:29:40.086
<i>Over here!</i>

01:29:40.214 --> 01:29:41.750
<i>It's me, sis.</i>

01:29:43.094 --> 01:29:44.726
<i>Do you want to make a movie?</i>

01:29:44.854 --> 01:29:48.086
<i>Oh. How about a scary one?</i>

01:29:48.214 --> 01:29:50.358
<i>I've been working on</i>
<i>this great script.</i>

01:29:51.830 --> 01:29:52.981
<i>Come on, Sid.</i>

01:29:53.462 --> 01:29:54.966
<i>We're family.</i>

01:29:55.094 --> 01:29:58.070
<i>It really comes down to</i>
<i>family, doesn't it, Sid?</i>

01:29:59.383 --> 01:30:02.998
<i>I mean, we both know how far</i>
<i>we'd go for our own family.</i>

01:30:04.150 --> 01:30:06.326
<i>And friends, of course.</i>

01:30:07.350 --> 01:30:10.198
<i>But all your friends die for</i>
<i>just being near you.</i>

01:30:10.839 --> 01:30:12.885
<i>I died for you, Sidney.</i>

01:30:14.101 --> 01:30:15.670
<i>Doesn't that</i>
<i>mean anything to you?</i>

01:30:15.798 --> 01:30:18.102
Where is my daughter?

01:30:18.966 --> 01:30:20.694
<i>I thought I'd go back to</i>
<i>where it all started.</i>

01:30:20.821 --> 01:30:23.158
<i>A phone call, a girl,</i>

01:30:23.287 --> 01:30:24.501
<i>and someone she cares about</i>

01:30:24.630 --> 01:30:27.510
<i>tied to a chair</i>
<i>outside of her house.</i>

01:30:32.789 --> 01:30:33.943
[groans]

01:30:34.070 --> 01:30:35.606
Okay. Okay.

01:30:37.334 --> 01:30:38.326
Okay.

01:30:43.670 --> 01:30:45.238
Tatum, baby, I'm sorry.

01:30:46.102 --> 01:30:47.093
Just...

01:30:48.566 --> 01:30:50.550
What do you want from me?
Please tell me.

01:30:53.301 --> 01:30:54.869
[groans, sniffles]

01:30:57.590 --> 01:30:58.486
You.

01:30:58.613 --> 01:31:01.014
Yeah. Me.

01:31:01.141 --> 01:31:03.830
Well, me and Karl.

01:31:03.958 --> 01:31:05.718
[Sidney] Karl is dead.
Mm-hmm.

01:31:06.678 --> 01:31:08.086
And I would be, too,

01:31:08.950 --> 01:31:11.189
but your daughter
missed my head.

01:31:12.149 --> 01:31:15.637
You've always got to
shoot them in the head.

01:31:15.766 --> 01:31:16.918
Okay, okay.

01:31:18.007 --> 01:31:19.446
Isn't that right,

01:31:20.085 --> 01:31:21.270
Stu?

01:31:22.326 --> 01:31:24.277
[Sidney breathes heavily]

01:31:28.886 --> 01:31:30.230
[whimpering]

01:31:30.358 --> 01:31:31.798
Okay, okay.

01:31:36.822 --> 01:31:38.421
[whispers]
I'll be right back.

01:31:43.638 --> 01:31:44.630
[grunts]

01:31:46.775 --> 01:31:48.118
[groaning]

01:31:48.950 --> 01:31:50.262
[grunts, pants]

01:31:50.901 --> 01:31:52.438
[Tatum whimpering]
Mark.

01:31:52.567 --> 01:31:53.527
Ah-ah-ah-ah.

01:31:53.654 --> 01:31:54.614
Okay.

01:31:54.741 --> 01:31:55.990
[groans]

01:31:57.238 --> 01:31:58.998
[groans]
[Marco chuckles]

01:31:59.926 --> 01:32:00.918
Look at that!

01:32:01.046 --> 01:32:02.806
He's still alive.

01:32:03.478 --> 01:32:04.790
That is a tough motherfucker.

01:32:04.918 --> 01:32:05.910
Fuck you!

01:32:11.799 --> 01:32:13.719
Jessica. What?

01:32:13.845 --> 01:32:15.157
Hi, neighbor.

01:32:15.830 --> 01:32:17.206
How you holding up?

01:32:17.814 --> 01:32:18.997
[Marco chuckles]

01:32:19.701 --> 01:32:21.846
You didn't really think
it was Stu?

01:32:22.966 --> 01:32:25.270
Because that'd be dumb.
Stu's dead.

01:32:25.973 --> 01:32:27.862
You know,
alive in spirit, but...

01:32:28.919 --> 01:32:30.007
dead.

01:32:30.134 --> 01:32:31.959
See,
I have a background in A.I.

01:32:32.085 --> 01:32:35.735
I was a Google security
specialist once upon a time.
Before Fallbrook.

01:32:35.863 --> 01:32:37.750
Bringing Stu back was my idea.

01:32:37.878 --> 01:32:39.413
No, no, no, no,
it was my idea.

01:32:39.543 --> 01:32:41.846
No, I just let you think
it was your idea.

01:32:41.974 --> 01:32:43.286
Jessica, please,
what are you doing?

01:32:43.415 --> 01:32:46.166
"Oh, Jessica." "Oh, please."
"Oh, what are you doing?"

01:32:46.295 --> 01:32:50.135
God, I don't recognize you.
I mean, what happened to you?

01:32:50.933 --> 01:32:52.630
You know, you've really
let me down, Sid.

01:32:52.758 --> 01:32:55.542
Listen to me. This isn't you.

01:32:55.670 --> 01:32:57.815
Whatever this is,
there's another way.

01:32:57.943 --> 01:32:59.030
Oh, I know.

01:32:59.158 --> 01:33:00.854
There's always another way.

01:33:00.981 --> 01:33:02.934
[chuckles, grunts]
Excuse me.

01:33:03.061 --> 01:33:06.006
You taught me that.
It's in your book.

01:33:07.638 --> 01:33:09.494
You saved my life, Sidney.

01:33:10.581 --> 01:33:11.926
Before you ruined it.

01:33:13.079 --> 01:33:15.159
You know about
my abusive marriage, right?

01:33:16.150 --> 01:33:18.390
I was really trapped,
and I couldn't see a way out.

01:33:18.517 --> 01:33:22.839
But then I read
<i>Out of Darkness</i>
by Sidney Prescott.

01:33:22.965 --> 01:33:24.599
Oh, it's such a great book!

01:33:24.727 --> 01:33:29.174
And then I realized that
your life, it comes down to
one simple truth.

01:33:30.997 --> 01:33:33.142
Sidney Prescott kills
the bad guy.

01:33:34.678 --> 01:33:36.119
That's your purpose.

01:33:36.982 --> 01:33:40.278
You are a real-life
scream queen.

01:33:40.919 --> 01:33:42.486
The final girl.

01:33:43.734 --> 01:33:45.687
God, you inspire me!

01:33:46.710 --> 01:33:50.358
So I started planning
and doing Pilates,

01:33:50.487 --> 01:33:53.238
and then I pulled a Sidney

01:33:53.367 --> 01:33:54.774
and I killed my husband!

01:33:54.901 --> 01:33:56.407
[both chuckling]

01:33:56.534 --> 01:33:58.646
[Jessica]
I got away with it, too.

01:33:59.734 --> 01:34:02.934
And I had you to thank for it.
[chuckling]

01:34:03.063 --> 01:34:04.438
But then you went away, Sid!

01:34:04.566 --> 01:34:06.198
And you didn't go to New York.

01:34:06.326 --> 01:34:08.823
A Ghostface attack
doesn't count
if you're not there.

01:34:08.950 --> 01:34:09.847
You disappeared.

01:34:09.974 --> 01:34:11.221
Why, Sidney?

01:34:11.350 --> 01:34:13.750
I wanted people to see
there was life after trauma.

01:34:13.878 --> 01:34:15.383
But there isn't for you!

01:34:16.630 --> 01:34:19.605
Trauma is your life.

01:34:20.375 --> 01:34:21.399
When you disappeared,

01:34:21.525 --> 01:34:23.478
do you know how much
that hurt me?

01:34:23.606 --> 01:34:26.167
I mean,
I couldn't fucking handle it!

01:34:26.294 --> 01:34:27.702
I checked myself
into a facility.

01:34:27.831 --> 01:34:29.398
Fallbrook.
That's where we met.

01:34:29.526 --> 01:34:31.895
Okay, I'm talking,
so don't interrupt me, okay?

01:34:32.023 --> 01:34:34.070
Great. Fuck.
Where the fuck was I?

01:34:34.198 --> 01:34:35.863
Shit. Fuck!

01:34:35.990 --> 01:34:38.134
New York. Pilates.
You disappeared.

01:34:38.262 --> 01:34:40.374
Fallbrook.
Fallbrook. Fallbrook, yes!

01:34:40.503 --> 01:34:42.997
It was the closest psychiatric
center that I could find

01:34:43.126 --> 01:34:45.846
because I had to be near you.

01:34:47.159 --> 01:34:51.863
And that finally brings us
to tonight.

01:34:51.990 --> 01:34:54.614
[Sidney]
Okay, Jessica, you're right,
I've been selfish.

01:34:54.743 --> 01:34:56.919
I can do better.
We can start over.

01:34:57.045 --> 01:34:58.710
I am starting over.

01:35:02.615 --> 01:35:03.926
By killing you.

01:35:05.399 --> 01:35:06.806
No more baggage.

01:35:07.701 --> 01:35:09.525
I am releasing it all.

01:35:10.454 --> 01:35:11.701
What about Lucas?
You have a son.

01:35:11.830 --> 01:35:14.199
Oh, no, no. He's gone, Sid.

01:35:14.325 --> 01:35:16.534
I mean, he was too much
like his father.

01:35:16.983 --> 01:35:18.165
And now

01:35:19.221 --> 01:35:21.110
I can have a new beginning.

01:35:25.366 --> 01:35:27.734
Do you think that you've been
a good mother to Tatum?

01:35:28.886 --> 01:35:31.830
I mean, you really haven't
taught her anything useful,
am I right?

01:35:31.957 --> 01:35:33.494
[scoffs]
[Jessica chuckles]

01:35:34.263 --> 01:35:36.566
You've kept the survivor
all to yourself.

01:35:36.694 --> 01:35:39.831
But that's okay.
Because I'm gonna teach her!

01:35:43.158 --> 01:35:45.687
She's gonna watch
her mother die.

01:35:45.815 --> 01:35:47.478
Just like you did.

01:35:48.790 --> 01:35:50.358
The cycle continues.

01:35:50.487 --> 01:35:51.447
No.

01:35:51.575 --> 01:35:53.367
[Jessica] You see,
it finally dawned on me.

01:35:54.423 --> 01:35:56.151
I don't need you.

01:35:56.279 --> 01:35:58.518
I mean, none of us do.
Let's face it,

01:35:58.646 --> 01:36:01.494
you're kind of past your prime
for a final girl.

01:36:02.039 --> 01:36:04.501
I'm creating Sidney 2.0.

01:36:05.398 --> 01:36:07.221
Watch closely, Tatum.

01:36:14.805 --> 01:36:16.021
Okay.

01:36:16.918 --> 01:36:18.167
Okay, honey,

01:36:18.294 --> 01:36:19.830
you're gonna need
to call an ambulance. Okay?

01:36:19.957 --> 01:36:20.758
What?

01:36:20.886 --> 01:36:22.390
Mom! No, wait!
Where are you going?

01:36:22.550 --> 01:36:23.414
Stay with your dad.

01:36:23.541 --> 01:36:25.621
No, no, no, no, Mom! God, no!

01:36:40.054 --> 01:36:41.238
[Jessica whispers] Sidney.

01:36:42.231 --> 01:36:44.470
Sidney...

01:36:44.598 --> 01:36:45.814
Please.

01:36:45.943 --> 01:36:46.935
[clattering]

01:36:47.063 --> 01:36:48.951
[boom box blares]
["Look Out For Me" playing]

01:37:01.783 --> 01:37:02.966
[music stops]

01:37:07.605 --> 01:37:08.917
[screams]

01:37:10.007 --> 01:37:10.998
[both grunting]

01:37:28.215 --> 01:37:30.167
Is that all you've got?
[screams]

01:37:33.335 --> 01:37:34.678
[screaming]

01:37:57.975 --> 01:37:58.967
Fuck!

01:38:18.327 --> 01:38:19.447
[Sidney panting, coughing]

01:38:19.574 --> 01:38:20.887
Are you okay?

01:38:21.814 --> 01:38:22.807
You got to shoot her
in the head.

01:38:22.935 --> 01:38:24.694
What?
Shoot her in the--

01:38:25.847 --> 01:38:26.678
Shit!

01:38:26.807 --> 01:38:28.854
Damn it. Okay.

01:38:33.431 --> 01:38:34.679
Come on.

01:38:39.318 --> 01:38:40.758
[screaming]

01:38:58.101 --> 01:38:59.383
You okay?

01:39:02.934 --> 01:39:05.367
I'm Sidney
fucking Prescott's daughter.

01:39:13.365 --> 01:39:14.838
Past my prime.

01:39:16.150 --> 01:39:17.301
Fuck you.

01:39:26.805 --> 01:39:29.238
This is Robbie Rivers
with an exclusive

01:39:29.367 --> 01:39:30.774
on the scene, live report,

01:39:30.902 --> 01:39:32.758
at the home of
police chief Mark Evans,

01:39:32.887 --> 01:39:35.606
where a bloody nightmare
has come to an end.

01:39:42.774 --> 01:39:44.054
[pained grunt]

01:39:50.710 --> 01:39:52.055
Network wants a live remote.

01:39:52.183 --> 01:39:54.263
No way. Too much blood loss.

01:39:54.390 --> 01:39:55.958
I can't hold a camera.

01:39:56.503 --> 01:39:57.911
I was hoping you'd do it.

01:39:58.038 --> 01:39:59.510
I do feel better.

01:39:59.638 --> 01:40:01.398
We're gonna need to frame out
the blood, though.

01:40:01.526 --> 01:40:02.967
I'll get the tripod.

01:40:25.207 --> 01:40:26.775
Thanks for ditching me.

01:40:28.150 --> 01:40:29.814
Seriously,
what was that about?

01:40:31.607 --> 01:40:34.551
You have always
had my back, Gale.

01:40:35.447 --> 01:40:36.823
I should have
gone to New York.

01:40:37.494 --> 01:40:39.031
I should have
been there for you.

01:40:39.158 --> 01:40:39.991
No, Sid.

01:40:40.118 --> 01:40:42.135
And I was wrong
about something.

01:40:42.806 --> 01:40:44.598
I do trust...

01:40:46.646 --> 01:40:48.023
I trust you.

01:40:57.463 --> 01:40:58.807
You want me to
drive you to the hospital?

01:40:58.934 --> 01:41:00.727
I'd love that.
Okay.

01:41:00.854 --> 01:41:02.039
Just give me a minute.

01:41:18.583 --> 01:41:21.175
This is exactly what
I didn't want for you.

01:41:23.318 --> 01:41:25.207
I don't think
it was up to you.

01:41:32.023 --> 01:41:33.878
Tatum was my best friend.

01:41:35.478 --> 01:41:37.398
She was funny,

01:41:38.263 --> 01:41:39.671
and outspoken.

01:41:40.341 --> 01:41:43.158
Said whatever was on her mind.

01:41:43.287 --> 01:41:44.598
No edit whatsoever.

01:41:46.295 --> 01:41:49.527
And she was strong.

01:41:49.910 --> 01:41:51.861
And fierce.

01:41:51.991 --> 01:41:55.350
She wasn't afraid of anything.

01:41:58.838 --> 01:42:01.718
So that's why
I named you Tatum.

01:42:02.487 --> 01:42:05.591
Because that was my wish

01:42:06.165 --> 01:42:07.351
for you.

01:42:09.014 --> 01:42:10.551
To be strong...

01:42:12.471 --> 01:42:14.007
and unafraid.

01:42:17.590 --> 01:42:19.095
What else can I tell you?

01:42:21.015 --> 01:42:22.647
That's enough for now.

01:42:24.758 --> 01:42:25.751
Okay.

01:42:29.558 --> 01:42:32.503
You know I love you.
I love you more.

01:42:35.255 --> 01:42:37.367
Let's go
see your dad.
Yeah.

01:43:08.662 --> 01:43:11.127
["Creepin" playing]

01:45:11.031 --> 01:45:13.143
Three, two...

01:45:13.271 --> 01:45:15.767
It all began
last Thursday night
in Woodsboro, California,

01:45:15.894 --> 01:45:18.359
at a house made infamous
for the stashing.

01:45:18.487 --> 01:45:21.654
Cut. I got caught between
"stabbing" and "slashing".

01:45:21.783 --> 01:45:22.710
Hey, you suck at this.

01:45:22.839 --> 01:45:23.864
Shut up. Go again.

01:45:23.991 --> 01:45:25.815
Copy that. Three, two...

01:45:26.583 --> 01:45:28.919
Hi. I'm Mindy Meeks-Mar--
I don't know.

01:45:29.047 --> 01:45:31.415
[Chad chuckling] You messed up
your own name, dude?

01:45:31.544 --> 01:45:34.615
Stop laughing!

01:45:36.631 --> 01:45:39.511
Okay. Three, two...

01:45:40.407 --> 01:45:42.327
Hi. I'm Mindy Meeks-Martin,

01:45:42.455 --> 01:45:43.895
three-time Ghostface survivor

01:45:44.024 --> 01:45:45.654
and new reporter
for CBS 7, New York.

01:45:45.783 --> 01:45:48.760
[Chad] Oh, my God, I wasn't
recording any of that.
One second.

01:45:48.886 --> 01:45:49.784
[Mindy] I hate you.

01:45:49.911 --> 01:45:51.862
["Twisting The Knife" playing]

01:49:02.806 --> 01:49:03.991
[music ends]
